{"id": "10643", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10643", "title": "The Shakedown", "text": "The Shakedown is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nQuick walkthrough.\nNote: if you step away from the fight and Elodi survive, the quest won't close.\nDetailed walkthrough.\nUpon entering &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy%20ghetto\"&gt;Fort Joy ghetto&lt;/a&gt; through the main entrance from the &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy%20beach\"&gt;beach&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; will encounter Elodi, Ifan, Burro and Kana to the left (east) of the steps to the waypoint shrine. On approaching the group, it becomes clear that Burro and Kana are shaking Elodi down; Ifan is largely observing at this stage. The Godwoken can choose to do nothing, which leads to Elodi fighting the two thieves with Ifan supporting her; alternatively one can take a side or pay the thugs to leave her be.\nIf one chooses to side with Burro and Kana, this will result in combat and the necessity to kill Ifan (thus losing him as a potential companion). Siding with Elodi allows for a peaceful resolution by either convincing the two that she is the brutal mythic Impaler (&lt;a href=\"Tag\"&gt;Outlaw&lt;/a&gt; required) or via threat of violence. If one chooses to trick the two humans into thinking they are being paid, this will lead to combat, but Burro will be disabled due to the kick in the knee.\nIf Burro and Kana were sided with, the quest will end after combat. If Elodi was assisted, one will have to follow her to the &lt;a href=\"Caverns%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;caverns&lt;/a&gt; and speak to her there once more.\nIf Elodi perishes, you have the opportunity to loot a &lt;a href=\"Severed%20Head\"&gt;Severed Head&lt;/a&gt; from her remains. Consuming the head grants an Elf the &lt;a href=\"First%20Aid%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;First Aid&lt;/a&gt; skill.\nThe optimal resolution to this quest involves aiding Elodi and subsequently conversing with her in the Caverns. In total, your endeavors yield 900 XP, a Severed Head imbued with the ability to grant First Aid, and a reward."}
