{"id": "12428", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12428", "title": "Thick of the Fight", "text": "Thick of the Fight is an &lt;a href=\"Warfare%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;adept Warfare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;source&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nThe more the merrier! Gain a damage boost for every nearby character for 2 turns.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 800 gold. Since is an adept Warfare skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 9.\nSince is a weapon based skill and as such it does not have a scroll. It is also not possible to craft a skillbook.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell warfare skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Gareth\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if his demands are met."}
{"id": "10745", "revid": "53578170", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10745", "title": "Thievery", "text": "Thievery is a &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;civil skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". \nDescription.\nThievery lets the player steal items from non-player characters, and unlock chests and doors. As the game progresses stealing and unlocking doors and chests will require higher Thievery levels.\nThievery allows each player character to steal once from non-player character per save file. In addition to aforementioned limit, there is also a limit on weight and value in items that can be stolen based on thievery skill level."}
