{"id": "2215", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2215", "title": "Throne Room", "text": "The Throne Room is your main room of operations in the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Tower\"&gt;Battle Tower&lt;/a&gt;. The there are two rooms you can enter, the throne room and your bedroom.\nThrone Room.\nIn the throne room there are five people you can interact with, your three &lt;a href=\"Runners\"&gt;Runners&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kirill\"&gt;Kirill&lt;/a&gt; a bard who can play songs for you, and a dancer named &lt;a href=\"Salome\"&gt;Salome&lt;/a&gt;. The most important part about the throne room is your &lt;a href=\"Runners\"&gt;Runners&lt;/a&gt; as they can be used to fetch gems, potion ingredients, and likewise.\nBedroom.\nThe bedroom is located down the elevator behind the throne. You can interact with &lt;a href=\"Hermaphroditus\"&gt;Hermaphroditus&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sassan\"&gt;Sassan&lt;/a&gt;, and your Coffer, a personal bank for you and the tower. You have the option in your inventory to right click items and send them to your Coffer at any point, or you can just teleport back and bank them. Your enchanter, alchemist, and necromancer will take the required resources from your coffer as they are needed. You do not have to have the ingredients on you."}
{"id": "12329", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12329", "title": "Throw Dust", "text": "Throw Dust is a &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; skill in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nThrow dust at a character, &lt;a href=\"Blinded%20%28Status%29\"&gt;blinding&lt;/a&gt; them and dealing earth damage. Clears surfaces and clouds in the area (including lava, source and deathfog).\nScales off level and Intelligence.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into both &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a any non-source &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks are combined. Since is a mixed skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from NPCs in the game."}
{"id": "12405", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12405", "title": "Throw Explosive Trap", "text": "Throw Explosive Trap is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; skill in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nThrow an explosive trap at target location. Trap takes 1 turn to activate. When active, the trap will explode when a character approaches it.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into both &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a any non-source &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks are combined. Since is a mixed skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll."}
{"id": "10415", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10415", "title": "Throwing Knife", "text": "Throwing Knife is a &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive scoundrel skill that allows caster to throw three knives at single opponent, dealing physical damage. Caster may backstab their foe if they shoot the knives at their opponent's back, dealing critical physical damage.\nSince requires a weapon it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Atrophy%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Atrophy&lt;/a&gt; status effect.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Scoundrel\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. Since is a starter Scoundrel skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Scoundrel skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well.\nSince is a weapon based skill and as such it does not have a scroll. It is also not possible to craft a skillbook.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus %) x (1 + Attribute Bonus % + Weapon Skill Bonus % + Misc Bonuses % ) x (1 + High Ground Bonus % + Crit Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Compatible attribute provides the lowest bonus out of the three (example: 3 points in Finesse are equal to 1 point of Warfare).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell scoundrel skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell."}
