{"id": "11556", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11556", "title": "Dimensional Bolt", "text": "Dimensional Bolt is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;starter Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nDimensional bolt is an offensive summoning skill that allows caster to shoot a bolt of elemental magic at their chosen target in 13 meter range. The bolt deals random type of damage and creates a corresponding surface at the location of impact (1 meter radius).\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Summoning%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Summoning Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a starter Summoning skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Summoning skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 70 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nLocation.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell summoning spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in."}
{"id": "14242", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14242", "title": "Dinner", "text": "Dinner is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Consumables\"&gt;consumable item&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a consumable item which when consumed will restore 20 % of maximum Vitality, grant + 2 bonus points to &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;. Characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; are healed for 40 % of maximum Vitality, gain + 4 bonus points to &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;. The effect of lasts 6 turns. \nPoisoned is a consumable item that was poisoned through various means (either &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Bottle%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;poison bottle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Zaikk%27s%20Talon\"&gt;Zaikk's Talon&lt;/a&gt;). Poisoning the will reduce its value to 0. Instead of healing it will deal poison damage equal to 20 % of the consumers maximum Vitality, rendering it unsafe for the living but safe for &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; and grant + 2 bonus points to &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;. The effects last 6 turns.\nIf character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; the will deal poison damage equal to 40 % of the consumers maximum Vitality and grant + 4 bonus points to &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;. The effects last 6 turns. \nNote that poisoned item may be used in crafting, however the end product will be un-poisoned item.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of food and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for. "}
