{"id": "22515", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22515", "title": "Divine Death", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20skills\"&gt;Divine Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nA divine skill unlocked through &lt;a href=\"Begin%20the%20Blessing%20Ritual\"&gt;the Blessing Ritual&lt;/a&gt;. The Divine may instantly kill anyone whose spiritual resistance is low enough or inflict large amount of damage upon them. Since it is a divine skill, it has no level requirement. This skill does not work on some enemies such as &lt;a href=\"Demon%20of%20Lies\"&gt;Demon of Lies&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis skill has a non-divine version called &lt;a href=\"Death%20Strike\"&gt;Death Strike&lt;/a&gt; which adds a small chance that a melee hit will instantly kill an enemy if their spiritual resistance is low enough. Unlike this skill, \"Death Strike\" can be learnt upon reaching level 24."}
{"id": "4189", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4189", "title": "Divine Descendant", "text": "Divine Descendant is a &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; that begins when you approach the &lt;a href=\"High%20Hall\"&gt;High Hall&lt;/a&gt; well in &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt; after completing &lt;a href=\"The%20Runes%20of%20Wrath\"&gt;The Runes of Wrath&lt;/a&gt;. A poor farmer, &lt;a href=\"Gobie\"&gt;Gobie&lt;/a&gt;, complains about a &lt;a href=\"ghost\"&gt;ghost&lt;/a&gt; haunting his house. A woman claiming to be a divine descendant named &lt;a href=\"Mona%20%28Ego%20Draconis%29\"&gt;Mona&lt;/a&gt; and her husband &lt;a href=\"Eamon\"&gt;Eamon&lt;/a&gt; offer to take care of the problem for a fee.\nDetailed Walkthough.\nThere are five methods to resolve this quest.\nMethod One:\nMethod Two:\nMethod Three:\nMethod Four:\nMethod Five (Requires at least 1 skill point on &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Ghost\"&gt;Summon Ghost&lt;/a&gt;):\nNote that methods one, three, four and five prevent you from gaining entry to Gobie's house, which contains a few chests and barrels to loot (the key to the locked chest is behind a crate and barrels near the ghost). In addition, methods three, four and five cost exp for mindreading. Nonetheless, method five is suggested as the most profitable way to resolve the quest, however will require you to use 1 skill point on &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Ghost\"&gt;Summon Ghost&lt;/a&gt; (which can be reverted at the &lt;a href=\"Training%20Arena\"&gt;Training Arena&lt;/a&gt; for a fee of 5000 gold). Gaining the skill through equipment is also possible and saves the 5000 gold."}
{"id": "3141", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3141", "title": "Divine Divinity", "text": "Divine Divinity is the first game in the \"Divinity\" &lt;a href=\"series\"&gt;series&lt;/a&gt;. It's a single-player fantasy computer role-playing game created by &lt;a href=\"Larian%20Studios\"&gt;Larian Studios&lt;/a&gt;, released in 2002. The game was re-released in 2004 along with \"&lt;a href=\"Beyond%20Divinity\"&gt;Beyond Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\" as a part of \"Beyond Divinity: Deluxe Edition\". \nStory.\nThe game takes place in &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;: a land that is slowly being torn apart by civil unrest, hatred, war, greed and several other melancholic happenings. These events point towards the possibility that dormant dark forces are once again attempting to surface. With potential doom on the rise and Rivellon in pieces, there is only one hope of saving the land from being consumed by Chaos: the discovery and ceremonial dubbing of the divine saviour of the Seven &lt;a href=\"Race\"&gt;Race&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCharacter Creation.\nCharacter Creation is a straightforward process in Divine Divinity. You begin with selecting either Male or Female and one of the three classes: &lt;a href=\"Warrior\"&gt;Warrior&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Survivor\"&gt;Survivor&lt;/a&gt;. Each character has their own biography and voice line. The player can choose a name, change the portrait and edit the &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20skills\"&gt;skills&lt;/a&gt;. Depending on the choice, the six attributes points scale differently with each class.\nThere are six statistics in the game:\n&lt;a href=\"Divinity%20Media\"&gt;Media&lt;/a&gt;.\nGuides.\nFollowing list shows generic guides and summary pages associated with Divine Divinity. For more specific guides for this game refer to: &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20Guides\"&gt;Divine Divinity Guides&lt;/a&gt;."}
