{"id": "14790", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14790", "title": "Divine Divinity Weapons", "text": "Weapons are the main source of damage in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\". The more powerful weapons have various &lt;a href=\"attribute\"&gt;attribute&lt;/a&gt; requirements that need to be met in order to equip and use them. Weapons may be &lt;a href=\"enchant\"&gt;enchant&lt;/a&gt;ed if they have &lt;a href=\"Enchant%20Weapon\"&gt;charm&lt;/a&gt; slots available.\n&lt;dpl&gt;\ncategory=Divine Divinity weapons\nuses = Template:Infobox weapon\nincludepage ={Infobox weapon}:type:rarity:req strength:req agility:damage:weight:value:durability\ntable=class=\"article-table sortable\",Name,Type,Rarity,Strength,Agility,Damage,Weight,Value,Durability\n&lt;/dpl&gt;"}
{"id": "18601", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18601", "title": "Divine Divinity World Objects", "text": "World objects are interactable items that can be found throughout &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;.\nContainers.\nContainers are used to store items. Some containers can be picked up to relocate them to a better place. Containers like barrels can be broken, but this action doesn't yield any practical purposes, unless they are locked. Breaking some types of containers will prevent them from being moved again, like the vases encountered in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth%20Catacombs\"&gt;Aleroth Catacombs&lt;/a&gt;.\nBookshelves/bookcases are a good (random) source of skillbooks for some &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20skills\"&gt;skills&lt;/a&gt; as well as some occasional gold and, of course, books and scrolls.\nChests can yield potentially useful items, like identifiable &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20Armour\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20Weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;. \nLocked containers can be empty sometimes however. There is no proper inventory management in &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;."}
