{"id": "12238", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12238", "title": "Dominate Mind", "text": "Dominate mind is an &lt;a href=\"Summoning%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;adept Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nDominate Mind charms an non-allied character, causing them to join you in combat for the duration of the status.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Summoning%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Summoning Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is an adept Summoning skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 9.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 50 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves varies. The cost to cast as a skill is 3 AP and the cost to cast as a scroll is only 1 AP.\nBoth the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell summoning spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in."}
{"id": "10647", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10647", "title": "Dominick", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"sourcerer\"&gt;sourcerer&lt;/a&gt; imprisoned on &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; in 1242 AD.\nBackground.\nDominick is a sourcerer and devout worshipper of &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; who spends his time praying at his shrine in &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy%20ghetto\"&gt;Fort Joy ghetto&lt;/a&gt;. He believes the other races like &lt;a href=\"elves\"&gt;elves&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"dwarves\"&gt;dwarves&lt;/a&gt; and especially &lt;a href=\"lizards\"&gt;lizards&lt;/a&gt; had caused the mortal races to fell in disfavour because of their \"blind devotion to source\". He also actively tries to persuade others to join in Endless Prayer."}
