{"id": "16875", "revid": "32621914", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16875", "title": "Dragon Knight Saga Quests", "text": "This page contains a list of all quests ' and its parts ' and \"\"."}
{"id": "2538", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2538", "title": "Dragon Knight Saga Skills", "text": "There are many different types of skills in \"\". \nOverview.\nHuman skills are broken down into warrior, ranger and wizard skills, but there is no strict class system (i.e. all characters can use skills from any of the three categories). Of these skills, some are passive skills which are always in effect, and other are active skills which can be used on the &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt;'s skill bar.\nIn the skill tree you can choose new skills, or improve existing skills, with skill points gained by leveling. &lt;a href=\"Skill%20Book\"&gt;Skill Book&lt;/a&gt;s also grant an extra skill point and can be found at various locations throughout &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. You can immediately see all of the available skills, but most have a level requirement that must be met. Some skills can be trained to an even higher level than initially shown on the skill tree; to do this you pay gold to a &lt;a href=\"Skill%20Trainer\"&gt;Skill Trainer&lt;/a&gt; to increase their maximum level. A skill trainer can also completely redo your skill choices at a cost.\nDragon.\n&lt;a href=\"Dragon\"&gt;Dragon&lt;/a&gt; skills can only be used in &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Form\"&gt;dragon form&lt;/a&gt; and are separate to human's, however, dragon skill points can be used to level them up. &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Skill%20Book\"&gt;Dragon Skill Book&lt;/a&gt;s can be found in many locations.\nCreature Skills.\n&lt;a href=\"Creature%20%28Undead%29\"&gt;The Creature&lt;/a&gt; uses different skills automatically depending on which &lt;a href=\"Creature%20Parts\"&gt;head&lt;/a&gt; is selected at the &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;necromancy circle&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "20853", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20853", "title": "Dragon Knight Saga Soundtrack", "text": ""}
{"id": "2282", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2282", "title": "Dragon Knight Saga Weapons", "text": "Weapons are items which can be equipped by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; and used in order to damage their enemies in \"\". There are four kinds of usable weapons, one-handed, two-handed, ranged weapons and shields. \nDescription.\nWeapons are items, which can be equipped by the Dragon Knight and utilised in combat. Their properties include: name (its color signifying its rarity), damage / armour values, properties, charms, enchantments and lastly a description. There are 8 types of rarity across the game:\nNote that all weapons above the uncommon rarity are either pre-equipped with or can have either charms or enchantments added to them, which add bonus &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills\"&gt;Skills&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Attributes\"&gt;Attributes&lt;/a&gt;. In addition to this, weapons can deal either \"melee damage\" or \"ranged damage\" and alongside one of these \"magic damage\".\nOne-Handed Weapons.\nOne-handed weapons can be wielded alone, in pairs, or alongside a shield. They have the fastest attack rate of all weapons, but with lower damage. These weapons, depending on how wielded, may benefit from &lt;a href=\"Single-handed%20Combat%20Expertise\"&gt;Single-handed Combat Expertise&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"One%20Hand%20and%20Shield%20Expertise\"&gt;One Hand and Shield Expertise&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dual%20Wielding\"&gt;Dual-Wielding Combat Expertise&lt;/a&gt;. When wielding a shield or another weapon in the off-hand, the attack speed is reduced compared to just a single weapon.\nShields.\nShields are defensive weapons which can be used only in left hand. They greatly boost the Dragon Knight's defensive abilities. \nTwo-Handed Weapons.\nTwo-Handed Weapons are weapons, which require both hands in order to be used, and therefore cannot be used alongside a \"shield\". They deal increased amount of damage, at the cost of attack speed. In \"Divinity II: Developer's Cut\" the only type of two-handed weapon is a \"two-handed sword\". \nRanged Weapons.\nRanged weapons are weapons capable of dealing damage at range. In \"Divinity II: Developer's Cut\" the only ranged weapon available to the Dragon Knight is the \"bow\". There are no arrow types and the amount of arrows is unlimited. Ranged weapon is required for Ranger skills. \nArmour and Weapon Sets.\nSome unique weapons and shields are part of a set. When set items are worn together they will either receive additional properties or their current bonuses will be increased. "}
