{"id": "3041", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3041", "title": "Dragon Slayers", "text": "Dragon Slayers are an elite military unit operating on &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; from roughly 1250 AD to 1300 AD. \nBackground.\nTraining to become a Dragon Slayer starts at a very young age, presumably less than 10 years old, and not many make it to become a Slayer. Slayers are trained in all three classes of combat: Warrior, Hunter, and Mage. They are the only &lt;a href=\"humans\"&gt;humans&lt;/a&gt;, not counting the human &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;dragon knights&lt;/a&gt;, that have learned to &lt;a href=\"Mindread\"&gt;read minds&lt;/a&gt;. Thanks to absorbing the memories of Dragons themselves, their eyes are colored silver and are capable of seeing the spirits of the long dead. The Order is led by an elite group of Slayers known as the Blood Echelon. \nThe Order of the Dragon Slayers was created by vengeful knights at the &lt;a href=\"Rivertown\"&gt;Rivertown&lt;/a&gt; cathedral that wanted justice for the death of &lt;a href=\"Lucian%20the%20Divine\"&gt;the Divine&lt;/a&gt; at the hands of a dragon knight in the Great War between 1244 AD and 1250 AD. The dragon slayers quickly went from a small band of knights to a mighty army of elites. Though they have lost many soldiers the result is clear, the numbers of the Dragon Knights dwindled. \nAs of 1300 AD, only a single Dragon Knight from the era of the Great War remained. She was known as &lt;a href=\"Talana\"&gt;Talana&lt;/a&gt; and has left many mutilated Dragon Slayer corpses in her wake , before being mortally wounded by Commander &lt;a href=\"Rhode\"&gt;Rhode&lt;/a&gt; and her fellow slayers, &lt;a href=\"Marius\"&gt;Marius&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gunther\"&gt;Gunther&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Gene\"&gt;Gene&lt;/a&gt;. \nIt is presumed the order was disbanded by Lucian after he was saved by the &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;last Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; from his imprisonment in &lt;a href=\"Plane%20of%20Hypnerotomachia\"&gt;Plane of Hypnerotomachia&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nSee also.\n&lt;a href=\"Books%20and%20notes%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;Book&lt;/a&gt;s about Dragon Slayers:"}
