{"id": "14829", "revid": "53418829", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14829", "title": "Drudanae", "text": "Drudanae is a potent herb found throughout &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nA highly addictive plant that is controlled in some parts of the world, Drudanae is commonly found in the possession of healers, adventurers, or criminal gangs. The plant itself is also prized by the &lt;a href=\"lizard\"&gt;lizard&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Dreams\"&gt;House of Dreams&lt;/a&gt; as it enhances their ability to dream and see visions. Due to its potency on the mind, the recommendation is to use it in rituals and avoid its use if one has a mental illness. Although the regulations differ by region in Rivellon, it is safer to assume that the plant is prohibited rather than allowed. However, there are recorded caveats for the legal possession of the drug by licensed healers due to its known medicinal purposes. Uncontrollable shaking is one of the known symptoms that addicts will experience during withdrawal. \nCultivation required lots of light, a warm, preferably indoor, atmosphere and regular watering.\nConsumption of the herb will lead to a slowing and calming of the mind, allowing the consumer a level of clarity and even inspiration. It should be stored in a dry container so as to be kept in a usable condition."}
{"id": "8175", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8175", "title": "Drudanae, a Manual", "text": "Drudanae, a Manual is a &lt;a href=\"book\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; describing the use and dangers of the &lt;a href=\"Drudanae%20%28Ego%20Draconis%29\"&gt;Drudanae&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"."}
{"id": "14826", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14826", "title": "Drudanae (Divine Divinity)", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20quest%20items\"&gt;quest item&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\"\nCharacteristics.\nA tall dark coloured plant, which is classed as a narcotic in the dukedom on &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt; in 1218 AD, it can only be grown by special dispensation. It is a hybrid of plants and cannot be found in the wild. In winter it must be kept indoors and in all seasons it must be kept in sunlight, but can be partially shaded in summertime."}
{"id": "8181", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8181", "title": "Drudanae (Ego Draconis)", "text": "Drudanae is a &lt;a href=\"Herbs\"&gt;herb&lt;/a&gt; in .\nDescription.\nDrudanae is an illicit herb that was used for healing and rituals in the past, but is now banned due its highly addictive nature. It can still be found being used for recreational purposes due to its effect on the brain. Users describe it as inspiring, relaxing, and capable of slowing down the mind. Drudanae should not be used by persons with psychological problems, or when operating heavy equipment such as a &lt;a href=\"zeppelin\"&gt;zeppelin&lt;/a&gt;.\nHarvesting a Drudanae plant yields enough for 2 to 5 uses, each of which can be sold for approximately 1,000 gold on the black market. It is typically ground for use in a healing salve, or dried and smoked when used recreationally."}
{"id": "11819", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11819", "title": "Drudanae (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Drudanae is a type of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Consumables%23Plants\"&gt;herb&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nDrudanae is a highly addictive herb which decreases &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; by 1 point and increases &lt;a href=\"Wits\"&gt;Wits&lt;/a&gt; by 2 points for 1 turn. The herbs effect last for 3 turns and will set &lt;a href=\"Slowed%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Slowed status&lt;/a&gt; upon the one who consumes it. \nGriff's Overpriced Drudanae is a Drudanae sold only by &lt;a href=\"Griff\"&gt;Griff&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy%20Ghetto\"&gt;Fort Joy Ghetto&lt;/a&gt; for extremely high price. It has the same effects as normal Drudanae. Note that it cannot be used to make &lt;a href=\"Drudanae%20Seedling\"&gt;Drudanae Seedling&lt;/a&gt;. \nDistinctive Drudanae is a rare type of Drudanae which can only be grown from &lt;a href=\"Drudanae%20Seedling\"&gt;Drudanae Seedling&lt;/a&gt;s placed upon oil surface. Note that in order to grow this herb and buy it the player must have activated Gift Bag: Herb Gardens.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for. "}
