{"id": "18145", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18145", "title": "Durability", "text": " is a statistic on equipment in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\", \"&lt;a href=\"Beyond%20Divinity\"&gt;Beyond Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\", ' and '.\n\"Divine/Beyond Divinity\".\nIn \"Divine/Beyond Divinity\" the condition of equipment is displayed on the HUD immediately to the bottom right of the character's vital statistics (the equipment icon). While all equipment has more than 25% of its durability remaining, the standard equipment icon is visible, however as an item falls below this threshold, the icon is replaced with a white hammer on a yellow background; opening the equipment menu will show the item with a yellow/orange background. The moment durability reaches 0 for an item, the background on the icon turns red and the item is visibly removed from &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt;. It also shows in a deep red in the menu."}
