{"id": "20197", "revid": "53418829", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20197", "title": "School's Out", "text": " is a in \"\".\nDetailed walkthrough.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Good%20Counsel%20School\"&gt;Good Counsel School&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Arx\"&gt;Arx&lt;/a&gt; is out of commission because of the drug addict squatters occupying the classroom in the north-east of the school. &lt;a href=\"Beryl%20Griff\"&gt;Beryl Griff&lt;/a&gt;, a teacher at this school, informs you of this problem in conversation with her and asks you to help her. If you imply you will deal with this problem by killing them, she will tell you to not use violence.\nYou can enter through the side door to the room filled with squatters and use one of the multiple Persuasion options to persuade &lt;a href=\"Sister%20Schori\"&gt;Sister Schori&lt;/a&gt; to leave along with the others, which awards 58,175 experience.\nUpon telling Beryl Griff of your success, the player can ask for payment or information as their reward, or tell her neither are needed. The player will receive a book of craftsmanship if they ask for payment. If they ask for information, she will tell them that &lt;a href=\"Linder%20Kemm\"&gt;Lord Linder Kemm&lt;/a&gt; must be keeping some secrets since he is suspicious; she will comment on the fact that he doesn't sleep in the same room as his wife for example."}
