{"id": "4484", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4484", "title": "Scorpion Belt", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Accessories\"&gt;special belt&lt;/a&gt; in \"\" and its previous versions.\nDescription.\n is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Accessories%23Earrings\"&gt;special belt&lt;/a&gt; and a component of the &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Set\"&gt;Scorpion Set&lt;/a&gt;, which is made out of &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Sword\"&gt;two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Cuirass\"&gt;cuirass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Gauntlets\"&gt;gauntlets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Bracelet\"&gt;bracelet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Necklace\"&gt;necklace&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Earrings\"&gt;earrings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Belt\"&gt;belt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Ring\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 27 in order to be worn. When worn the belt will boost Hitpoint Regeneration (HP Regeneration) by 0.07 points and increase Hitpoints by 43 points. The belt have 1 enchantment slot. The default enchantment is Damage Aura.\nHow to Obtain.\nIt is found in a chest within &lt;a href=\"Stone%27s%20Flying%20Fortress\"&gt;Stone's Flying Fortress&lt;/a&gt;.\nSet Properties.\nScorpion Belt are a part of the set Scorpion Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Scorpion Belt primary increased attribute is HP Regeneration, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
{"id": "4487", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4487", "title": "Scorpion Bracelet", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Accessories%23Bracelet\"&gt;special bracelet&lt;/a&gt; in \"\" and its previous versions.\nDescription.\nScorpion Bracelet is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special bracelet&lt;/a&gt; and a component of the &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Set\"&gt;Scorpion Set&lt;/a&gt;, which is made out of &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Sword\"&gt;two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Cuirass\"&gt;cuirass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Gauntlets\"&gt;gauntlets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Bracelet\"&gt;bracelet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Necklace\"&gt;necklace&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Earrings\"&gt;earrings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Belt\"&gt;belt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Ring\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 21 in order to be worn. When worn the bracelet will boost Conditioned Body by 4 points and &lt;a href=\"Death%20Blow\"&gt;Death Blow&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; by 1 point. The bracelet has 1 enchantment slot. The default enchantment is Magic Damage Aura.\nHow to Obtain.\nThe bracelet can be found upon the body of the Imp Boss at the &lt;a href=\"Imps%27%20Lair\"&gt;Imps' Lair&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt;. \nSet Properties.\nScorpion Bracelet are a part of the set Scorpion Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Scorpion Bracelet primary increased attribute is &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
{"id": "4483", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4483", "title": "Scorpion Cuirass", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special armour&lt;/a&gt; in \"\" and its previous versions.\nDescription.\nScorpion Cuirass is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special cuirass&lt;/a&gt; and is a component of the &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Set\"&gt;Scorpion Set&lt;/a&gt;, which is made out of &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Sword\"&gt;two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Cuirass\"&gt;cuirass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Gauntlets\"&gt;gauntlets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Bracelet\"&gt;bracelet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Necklace\"&gt;necklace&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Earrings\"&gt;earrings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Belt\"&gt;belt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Ring\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 24 in order to be worn. When worn the cuirass will boost Melee Armour Rating by 4 points and Magic Armour Rating by 3 points. The cuirass has 1 charm slot and 2 enchantment slots. The default enchantment are Increased Mana and Life Line.\nHow to Obtain.\nCan be bought from &lt;a href=\"Artemas\"&gt;Artemas&lt;/a&gt; a trader at &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Cliff%20Castle\"&gt;Dragon Cliff Castle&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt;.\nSet Properties.\nScorpion Cuirass is a part of the set Scorpion Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Scorpion Cuirass primary increased attribute is Melee Armour Rating, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
{"id": "4486", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4486", "title": "Scorpion Earrings", "text": " are a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Accessories\"&gt;special earrings&lt;/a&gt; in \"\" and its previous versions.\nDescription.\n are a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Accessories%23Earrings\"&gt;special earrings&lt;/a&gt; and a component of the &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Set\"&gt;Scorpion Set&lt;/a&gt;, which is made out of &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Sword\"&gt;two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Cuirass\"&gt;cuirass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Gauntlets\"&gt;gauntlets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Bracelet\"&gt;bracelet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Necklace\"&gt;necklace&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Earrings\"&gt;earrings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Belt\"&gt;belt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Ring\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 29 in order to be worn. When worn the earrings will boost Conditioned Body by 4 points and &lt;a href=\"Whirlwind%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;Whirlwind&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; by 1 point. The earrings have 1 enchantment slot. The default enchantment is Retribution Aura.\nHow to Obtain.\nIt is found in a golden chest within &lt;a href=\"Keara%27s%20Flying%20Fortress\"&gt;Keara's Flying Fortress&lt;/a&gt;.\nSet Properties.\nScorpion Earrings are a part of the set Scorpion Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Scorpion Earrings primary increased attribute is Conditioned Body, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
{"id": "4480", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4480", "title": "Scorpion Gauntlets", "text": " are a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special gauntlets&lt;/a&gt; in \"\" and its previous versions.\nDescription.\nScorpion Gauntlets are a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special gauntlets&lt;/a&gt; and is a component of the &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Set\"&gt;Scorpion Set&lt;/a&gt;, which is made out of &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Sword\"&gt;two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Cuirass\"&gt;cuirass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Gauntlets\"&gt;gauntlets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Bracelet\"&gt;bracelet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Necklace\"&gt;necklace&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Earrings\"&gt;earrings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Belt\"&gt;belt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Ring\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 24 in order to be worn. When worn the gauntlets will boost Melee Armour Rating by 3 points and &lt;a href=\"Spirit\"&gt;Spirit&lt;/a&gt; attribute by 6 points. The gauntlets have 2 enchantment slots. The default enchantment is Life Line.\nHow to Obtain.\nFound in a chest inside the &lt;a href=\"Primordial%20Cave\"&gt;Primordial Cave&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt;. The main quest &lt;a href=\"Reaping%20the%20Seeds\"&gt;Reaping the Seeds&lt;/a&gt; needs to be completed in order to access it. \nSet Properties.\nScorpion Gauntlets are a part of the set Scorpion Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Scorpion Gauntlets primary increased attribute is Indomitable Will, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
{"id": "4481", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4481", "title": "Scorpion Helmet", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special helmet&lt;/a&gt; in \"\" and its previous versions.\nDescription.\nScorpion Helmet is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special helmet&lt;/a&gt; and is a component of the &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Set\"&gt;Scorpion Set&lt;/a&gt;, which is made out of &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Sword\"&gt;two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Cuirass\"&gt;cuirass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Gauntlets\"&gt;gauntlets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Bracelet\"&gt;bracelet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Necklace\"&gt;necklace&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Earrings\"&gt;earrings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Belt\"&gt;belt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Ring\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 23 in order to be worn. When worn the helmet will boost &lt;a href=\"Vitality\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spirit\"&gt;Spirit&lt;/a&gt; attribute by 5 points each. The helmet has 2 charm slots and 1 enchantments slot. The default enchantment is Melee Protection.\nHow to Obtain.\nIt can be obtained as loot dropped from a member of the 'Dragon Terror Patrol' at &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Cliff%20Castle\"&gt;Dragon Cliff Castle&lt;/a&gt; after completing the quest &lt;a href=\"Down%20the%20Hatch\"&gt;Down the Hatch&lt;/a&gt;.\nSet Properties.\nScorpion Helmet is a part of the set Scorpion Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Scorpion Helmet primary increased attribute is &lt;a href=\"Vitality\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
