ipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
{"id": "4488", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4488", "title": "Scorpion Ring", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Accessories%23Rings\"&gt;special ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"\" and its previous versions.\nDescription.\nScorpion Cuirass is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special cuirass&lt;/a&gt; and is a component of the &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Set\"&gt;Scorpion Set&lt;/a&gt;, which is made out of &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Sword\"&gt;two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Cuirass\"&gt;cuirass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Gauntlets\"&gt;gauntlets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Bracelet\"&gt;bracelet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Necklace\"&gt;necklace&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Earrings\"&gt;earrings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Belt\"&gt;belt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Ring\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 24 in order to be worn. When worn the ring will boost HP Regeneration and Mana Regeneration by 0.07 points each. The ring has 3 charm slots and 1 enchantment slot. The default enchantment is Poison Aura.\nHow to Obtain.\nFound at &lt;a href=\"Kali%27s%20Flying%20Fortress\"&gt;Kali's Flying Fortress&lt;/a&gt; at the end of Rivertown Gorge. It is inside a chest on the lowest part of the first large island. \nSet Properties.\nScorpion Ring is a part of the set Scorpion Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Scorpion Ring primary increased attribute is Hitpoints, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
{"id": "3989", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3989", "title": "Scorpion Set", "text": "Scorpion Gauntlets\nOBTAINED: Locked inside a plain wooden chest in the Primordial Cave, very near the platform from which you meet the Patriarch. The key is on a piece of wooden scaffolding in the back of the same room of the cave, in the opposite direction.\nScorpion Helmet\nOBTAINED: Dropped by the head of the Dragon Terror Patrol, Tibus, in Dragon Cliff Castle. To fight them, complete the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Down%20the%20Hatch\"&gt;Down the Hatch&lt;/a&gt;\".\nScorpion Leggings\nOBTAINED: Purchased from &lt;a href=\"Sam\"&gt;Sam&lt;/a&gt; in the Shipwreck Camp on &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island\"&gt;Sentinel Island&lt;/a&gt;.\nScorpion Cuirass\nOBTAINED: Purchased from &lt;a href=\"Artemas\"&gt;Artemas&lt;/a&gt; in Dragon Cliff Castle in the &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt;.\nScorpion Belt\nOBTAINED: In a large golden chest in Stone's flying fortress. This chest is on an altar on a small island in the northwestern part of the fortress. It is beneath the large island housing the fortress with the teleporter leading to\ninside the anti-dragon barrier. The area glows blue, and there are large walls with faces on them looking at the chest. Difficult to describe, but very easy to find (look for the island with a lone Lightning Tower).\nScorpion Necklace\nOBTAINED: In a large wooden chest west of the &lt;a href=\"Wayshrine%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;Beach Shrine&lt;/a&gt; on Sentinel Island.\nThis chest is locked with Mister Shiny, a key given as a reward for the &lt;a href=\"Hermit\"&gt;Hermit&lt;/a&gt;'s quest \"&lt;a href=\"From%20Soup%20to%20Nuts\"&gt;From Soup to Nuts&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nScorpion Bracelet\nOBTAINED: Dropped by the Imp Boss in the Imps' Lair in Orobas Fjords. It is inside the final room of the cave, and you suffer constant fire damage until he dies.\nScorpion Ring\nOBTAINED: In a golden chest on the northern continent of &lt;a href=\"Kali\"&gt;Kali&lt;/a&gt;'s flying fortress. This is found in an alcove on the southern side, on the lower tier of land. The area glows blue, so it is difficult to miss.\nScorpion Sword\nOBTAINED: In a golden chest inside the Lost Tomb, as part of the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Grave%20Robbers\"&gt;Grave Robbers&lt;/a&gt;\". There are three levers to throw: one near the casket in the central area, one on some wooden scaffolding in the back of the tomb, and one behind some breakable crates, also in the back."}
{"id": "4489", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4489", "title": "Scorpion Sword", "text": "Scorpion Sword is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Weapons%23Two-Handed%20Weapons\"&gt;special two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"\" and its previous versions.\nDescription.\nScorpion Sword is a special weapon and part of the &lt;a href=\"Scorpion\"&gt;Scorpion&lt;/a&gt; set, which is made out of &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Sword\"&gt;two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Cuirass\"&gt;cuirass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Gauntlets\"&gt;gauntlets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Bracelet\"&gt;bracelet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Necklace\"&gt;necklace&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Earrings\"&gt;earrings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Belt\"&gt;belt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Scorpion%20Ring\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 26 in order to be equipped. When equipped the sword will boost &lt;a href=\"Conditioned%20Body\"&gt;Conditioned Body&lt;/a&gt; by 3 points, Hitpoints by 43 points and &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; attribute by 5 points. The sword has 2 charm slots and 3 enchantments slots. The default enchantment is Increased Damage.\nHow to Obtain.\nFound in chest located in &lt;a href=\"Lost%20Tomb\"&gt;Lost Tomb&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt;. The tomb is unlocked through quest &lt;a href=\"Grave%20Robbers\"&gt;Grave Robbers&lt;/a&gt;.\nSet Properties.\nScorpion Sword is a part of the set Scorpion Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Scorpion Sword primary increased attribute is Melee Damage, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
{"id": "21473", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21473", "title": "Scoundrel", "text": ""}
{"id": "17673", "revid": "2056997", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17673", "title": "Scoundrel (DOS EE)", "text": ""}
{"id": "6145", "revid": "54598427", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6145", "title": "Scoundrel (Original Sin)", "text": "Scoundrel skills have access to the most Status Effects besides Witchcraft, but deal damage as they inflict them. With almost half of the skills requiring a dagger to be equipped, this is a skill tree best dipped into for &lt;a href=\"Fast%20Track\"&gt;Fast Track&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Walk%20in%20Shadows\"&gt;Walk in Shadows&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20and%20Dagger\"&gt;Cloak and Dagger&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Charming%20Touch\"&gt;Charming Touch&lt;/a&gt;. Otherwise the damage is lower than the other physical abilities; often if a dagger is equipped for 2 AP to attack, attacking 4 times and using Daggers Drawn exactly equal.\nDivinity: Original Sin.\nThere are 3 abilities available in the Scoundrel tree, based on the skill level:\nLevel 5 of Scoundrel is not required by any skill and only unlocks the talent \"Headstrong\" which makes the character more resistant to being immobilized.\nEnhanced Edition.\nThe bracket after the CD of each skill indicates the minimum cooldown (achieved when DEX is 15 or higher).\n\u221e) Can only be used once per combat."}
