{"id": "12239", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12239", "title": "Shadow Infusion", "text": "Shadow Infusion is an &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;adept Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive summoning skill that allows caster to imbue their summoned Incarnate for 3 turns or until the Incarnate expires. The skill will allow the Incarnate to cast &lt;a href=\"Chameleon%20Cloak\"&gt;Chameleon Cloak&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Corrupted%20Blade\"&gt;Corrupted Blade&lt;/a&gt; skills whilst increasing their Damage by 25 % and Movement + 1 point. \nUnlike elemental infusion skills, this infusion skill can be combined with other infusion skills such as &lt;a href=\"Farsight%20Infusion\"&gt;Farsight Infusion&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Infusion\"&gt;Fire Infusion&lt;/a&gt; without it being cancelled. This skill however can be used only on the Incarnate and cannot be used on other summoned creatures and totems.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. Since is an adept Summoning skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 9.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive skill that provides clear set bonuses. As such these bonuses by themselves cannot be increased, however they can stack with other items, skills or talents that provide them.\n skill properties can be affected by talents and other skills only.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell summoning spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift Bag: Pet Power allows this skill to be used on any summoned creature. This gift bag also shortens the cooldown of this skill from 3 turns to 1 turn. Following table shows what skills will specific summoned entity gain from . Note that there are no changes to the skill and bonuses granted by the skill to the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;, likewise all summoned entities gain warfare skill &lt;a href=\"Chameleon%20Cloak\"&gt;Chameleon Cloak&lt;/a&gt;."}
