{"id": "5011", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5011", "title": "Shadowblade (Original Sin)", "text": "Shadowblade is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%20Classes\"&gt;survivor class&lt;/a&gt; in ' and the '.\nBackground.\nWhen the sorcerer went mad, only those who could flee were spared a terrible death. The fleet-footed shadowblade escaped, but the rest of the village did not.\nAs a wandering orphan, thieves, beggars, pirates, and murderers taught the shadowblade that man was no more than a beast, and the laws of nature were simple: Kill or be killed; eat or go hungry.\nBut a survivor among survivors needed an advantage. Posing as the child of nobleman, it was almost easy to gain access to the Academy of the &lt;a href=\"Source%20Hunter\"&gt;Source Hunter&lt;/a&gt;s. Here the most elite secrets of magic were offered freely, and \nthe shadowblade perfected them all.\nBy the time the ruse was discovered, it was too late. The academy had a prized pupil, and the shadowblade had found that hunting sorcerers satisfied the soul better than picking pockets. Usually.\nStarting statistics.\nFollowing table shows all statistics, spells and items of the Shadowblade at the start of the game. There are some differences differences between \"Classic\" and \"Enhanced\" versions of the game including changes in stats, abilities, skills and items at their disposal. \nIn Enhanced Edition the Shadowblades ability &lt;a href=\"Single-handed%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;Single-handed&lt;/a&gt; (from Classic) got replaced with &lt;a href=\"Dual%20Wielding\"&gt;Dual Wielding&lt;/a&gt;. All of their skills from Classic Edition got replaced with new ones in Enhanced Edition. Reflecting the ability change the Shadowblade wields alongside the &lt;a href=\"Fighting%20Knife\"&gt;Fighting Knife&lt;/a&gt; also the &lt;a href=\"Training%20Sword%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Training Sword&lt;/a&gt; in their second hand. Another difference is that instead of 1 Minor Healing potion they have 2 Minor Healing potions and their &lt;a href=\"Blind%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Blind scroll&lt;/a&gt; got replaced with &lt;a href=\"Toxic%20Grenade\"&gt;Toxic Grenade&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "10593", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10593", "title": "Shadowblade (Original Sin 2)", "text": "The Shadowblade is a &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;survivor class&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nSummary.\nShadowblade is a survivor relying on &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; magic in addition to their &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; skill. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wits\"&gt;Wits&lt;/a&gt;. They mainly wield a single dagger. \nTheir first starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Backlash\"&gt;Backlash&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to teleport themselves behind their foe and deal damage to them. The second starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Chicken%20Claw\"&gt;Chicken Claw&lt;/a&gt; spell which allows them to transform their foe into harmless chicken and their final starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Chameleon%20Cloak\"&gt;Chameleon Cloak&lt;/a&gt; that allows them to become invisible. The potential of this skill is further enhanced by their talent Guerilla which increases their damage dealt when sneaking by 40 %.\nTheir civil talent is &lt;a href=\"Thievery\"&gt;Thievery&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to unlock locked doors, chests and to lighten the pockets of overly wealthy merchants. \nMercenary Shanova.\nPestilence is an &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be &lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Recruiting%20Mercenaries\"&gt;hired&lt;/a&gt; from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. Her role on the battlefield is that of shadowblade, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Survivor%20classes\"&gt;survivor&lt;/a&gt; using &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scoundrel skills&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;Polymorph magic&lt;/a&gt; to decimate her foes.\nDetailed description.\nList of all skills available.\nShadowblade is a class focused on casting &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Scoundrel\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; skills and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; spells. Following table shows all skills and spells which Shadowblade can learn as they level up and invest points in respective combat abilities."}
{"id": "19229", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19229", "title": "Shadows (potion)", "text": "The shadows potions are a type of &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20consumables\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nBlack liquid in glass vial. When consumed, they provide temporary invisibility in form of &lt;a href=\"Fade%20From%20Sight\"&gt;Fade From Sight&lt;/a&gt;, consuming 1 &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; per second. Any interaction aside from movement, running out of magic or drinking another potion will cancel invisibity.\nThey can be created by combining &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Potion\"&gt;Magic Potion&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20Potion\"&gt;Stamina Potion&lt;/a&gt; and increased in size with &lt;a href=\"Augmentor\"&gt;Augmentor&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocations.\nSold by potion vendors."}
