{"id": "20217", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20217", "title": "Shocked (Status)", "text": "Shocked is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nShocked is a negative environmental &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; caused by afflicted character being shocked with electricity. It is accompanied by several debuffs and may lead to &lt;a href=\"Stunned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Stunned&lt;/a&gt; status effect. Negative effects caused being Shocked include:\nCause.\nThere are many ways through which burning status effect can be triggered. On &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; it is the contact with any electrified \"blood\" or \"water\" surface or clouds. In combat Shocked can be caused by myriad of items or most commonly &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; spells. \nTreatment.\nShocked is a status effect tied to air element and as such damages Magic armour before its shocking effect takes place. There are only two status effects that negate Shocked: &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Shell%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Magic Shell&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Permafrost%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Permafrost&lt;/a&gt;. If there are no viable means of reverting the status, then the best way to avoid damage to Vitality is by keeping Magic armour above 0. All consumable items that restore Magic armour can be strengthened by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; or by increasing &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; combat skill which increases Magic armour gained and given. As last resort Magic armour can be gained back through &lt;a href=\"Perseverance\"&gt;Perseverance&lt;/a&gt; but it will only work if character has been incapacitated. \nStatus removal.\nShocked can be removed only through spells or scrolls or a &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin%20Potion\"&gt;Stoneskin Potion&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "17005", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17005", "title": "Shocking Arrow", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a special arrow which deals air damage and inflicts &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked Status&lt;/a&gt; (for 1 turn) if the Magic Armour of affected characters reaches 0. Additionaly this arrow will electrify any blood or water surface (and clouds) at the area of impact. Note that if character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked Status&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Wet%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Wet Status&lt;/a&gt; this arrow will cause the character to be affected by &lt;a href=\"Stunned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Stunned Status&lt;/a&gt;. \nCharacters need to wield &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Weapons\"&gt;bow or crossbow&lt;/a&gt; in order to use this arrow. The damage of the arrow depends on: base damage of the wielded weapon, &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and height (bonus from height difference is affected by &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt;).\nSince is a special arrow it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Arrow Recovery&lt;/a&gt; talent which grants 33 % chance to recover a special arrow after firing it. This arrow is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Elemental Ranger&lt;/a&gt; talent that grants additional elemental damage bonus depending on the surface the shooting character is standing in. It is possible to increase the range of the arrow by 2 meters through the &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent.\nLocations.\nCreatures and Unnamed NPCs.\nFollowing table shows all creatures which have a chance to drop the item upon death. Highlighted creatures in this table have 100 % chance to drop said item. Note that creatures may drop other items as well."}
