{"id": "2435", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2435", "title": "Sibling Rivalry", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDetailed Walkthrough.\nThis quest begins after entering Forlorn Cave, which is located in a cove underneath &lt;a href=\"Sassan\"&gt;Sassan&lt;/a&gt;'s Tombstone. Player can either pick sides with either &lt;a href=\"Adah\"&gt;Adah&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Mahalath\"&gt;Mahalath&lt;/a&gt;, or simply defeat them both.\nSiding with Adah.\nIf the player sides with Adah by claiming her Dragon Elves are stronger, both sisters will ran of to their camps. Follow Adah by running to the left side of the cave and speak with her. \nShe will ask you to retrieve her Fake Red Ore, which is found in a chest (along with some random loot) on a shipwreck next to &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island%20Encampment\"&gt;Starbound Encampment&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce you got the ore go back to Forlorn Cave and speak with Adah. She will tell you to bring the Fake ore to Mahalath in order to malfunction her Walking Armour producing machinery. \nTo enter Mahalaths camp go straight from Adah's camp. Once you enter her camp Mahalath will engage in conversation with you. To proceed the quest tell her \"I had some red ore to spare, so... \" &lt;a href=\"Mindread\"&gt;Mindreading&lt;/a&gt; her will hint that her ore is being delivered by bandits and therefore hint at the best possible dialogue option (Mindreading is not neccessary since the option is already there). By telling her you stole the ore from Laiken's troops she will take the ore from you. \nIf you tell her you are there to sabotage her machinery she will attack you and thus fail the quest. If you tell Adah that you killed her sister in self defense she will attack you.\nAfter you had given Mahalath Fake red ore go back to Adah and speak with her. She will ran of to challenge her sister one last time and reward you.\nSiding with Mahalath.\nIf the player sides with Mahalath by claiming her Walking Armours are stronger, both sisters will ran of to their camps. Follow Mahalath by running to the right side of the cave and speak with her. \nShe will ask you to retrieve her Wolfsbane Poison, which is found in a chest (along with some random loot) next to &lt;a href=\"Laiken%27s%20Study\"&gt;Laiken's Study&lt;/a&gt; and behind &lt;a href=\"Allan%20%28Sentinel%20Island%29\"&gt;Allan&lt;/a&gt;'s camp.\nBring the poison to Mahalath. She will give you a poisoned Dragon Elf named Alfie and tell you to return it to Adah in order to weaken the rest of the Dragon Elves. \nGo straight from Mahalath's camp. Adah will immediately engage in conversation with you regarding the Dragon Elf. Tell her: \"I saved him from the evil clutches of your sister.\". Mindreading her will hint the best explanation for why you are returning her Dragon Elf. The mindreading is not neccessary however so telling her: \"I told her Laiken wants the best legions he can get, so no cheating.\"\", will make her accept the Dragon Elf. \nIf you tell Adah the Elf is poisoned she will become hostile and fail the quest. If you tell Mahalath you killed her sister in self defense she will attack you.\nReturn to Mahalath and tell her you returned the Elf. She will reward you and ran of to face her sister.\nSiding against both sisters.\nIf the player claimed they are stronger than both sisters and their minions, they will all become hostile to the player.\nAdah is level 20 and Mahalath is level 16. Killing both of them will complete the quest."}
{"id": "8629", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8629", "title": "Siege of Orobas Bracers", "text": " are a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special bracers&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nLocation.\nCan be purchased from &lt;a href=\"Gofannon\"&gt;Gofannon&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Armour%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;er and merchant located south of the &lt;a href=\"Ministry\"&gt;Ministry&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Market\"&gt;Great Market&lt;/a&gt; district of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;. The price for the bracers is 33 540 gold but it can be lowered by &lt;a href=\"mindread\"&gt;mindread&lt;/a&gt;ing &lt;a href=\"Gofannon\"&gt;Gofannon&lt;/a&gt; to 25 155 gold."}
