{"id": "11678", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11678", "title": "Silencing Stare", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;master Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive necromancer skill that allows caster to curse the hostile characters in their sight (cone area) up to 13 meters. All hostile characters affected by the skill will take Magic Armour damage. Characters without Magic Armour are afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; status effect that makes them unable to cast magic-based skills for 1 turn.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Necromancy\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. \nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 1400 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Necromancy%20Skillbook\"&gt;High Tier Blank Necromancy Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a master Necromancer skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 16.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 350 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nSince does Magic Armour damage it will never damage Vitality of affected characters. This damage cannot be further improved through abilities, only the level and amount points invested in Intelligence attribute affects the damage done. Since destroys only the Magic Armour it will never benefit from the Necromancer ability as it calculates healing based on the damage done to Vitality itself.\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell necromancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only \"&lt;a href=\"Tarquin\"&gt;Tarquin&lt;/a&gt;\" is guaranteed to follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; as they travel with &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;. \"&lt;a href=\"Jahan\"&gt;Jahan&lt;/a&gt;\" may join the Godwoken on the ship as well if his demands are met. "}
{"id": "10615", "revid": "37473722", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10615", "title": "Silent Monk", "text": "Silent monks are former &lt;a href=\"Sourcerer\"&gt;Sourcerer&lt;/a&gt;s who have been drained of their &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; by the &lt;a href=\"The%20Magisters\"&gt;Magisters&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Order\"&gt;Divine Order&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nThe majority of silent monks were those who have been identified as Sourcerers, who were then &lt;a href=\"Source%20collar\"&gt;collared&lt;/a&gt; and sent to the island prison &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Reapers%27%20Eye\"&gt;Reapers' Eye&lt;/a&gt; by the Divine Order. Although the pretext of this was to keep the world safe from the &lt;a href=\"voidwoken\"&gt;voidwoken&lt;/a&gt;, the reality was that they were purged of their &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; energy and condemned to be thralls of the Magisters that purged them. This, however, is happening outside of the knowledge and approval of the &lt;a href=\"Paladins\"&gt;Paladins&lt;/a&gt; (oldest faction within the Divine Order), who sent &lt;a href=\"Cork\"&gt;Cork&lt;/a&gt; to Fort Joy to investigate their suspicions. \nStripped of their freedom and self thought, silent monks are barely alive, with only their physical characteristics to reflect who they were. They do still retain the skills they had prior to the purge--humans are physically strong, elves are magically imbued etc.\nLoot Table.\nFort Joy Prison.\nFollowing table shows all possible items which can be found in the corpse of the defeated creature."}
