{"id": "2809", "revid": "43400826", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2809", "title": "Sinister Cavern", "text": "THe Sinister Cavern is a cave system accessed by &lt;a href=\"The%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;The Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nDescription.\nThe Sinister Cavern is a &lt;a href=\"location\"&gt;location&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt; up a waterfall at the end of the little river that makes it. Inside you will find abominations and reach a cavernous area of lava with some nest towers spawning enemies and a &lt;a href=\"necromancer\"&gt;necromancer&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Barnabus\"&gt;Barnabus&lt;/a&gt; on a shielded platform.\nYou have to take your &lt;a href=\"dragon\"&gt;dragon&lt;/a&gt; form to get around and take teleporters to rooms with more abominations and shield generators that are shut off via lever. \nOne of these areas (there are three) contains the Book of the Dead needed to complete the &lt;a href=\"Book%20of%20the%20Dead\"&gt;Book of the Dead&lt;/a&gt; quest given by &lt;a href=\"Igor\"&gt;Igor&lt;/a&gt; at your &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Tower\"&gt;Battle Tower&lt;/a&gt; (if you chose him). Once you shut them all off, you can face Barnabus who will also summon an abomination to help him and he will heal it on occasion. Kill him and you will get his mace which is proof of his death for the &lt;a href=\"A%20Hunting%20We%20Shall%20Go%20Again\"&gt;A Hunting We Shall Go Again&lt;/a&gt; quest as he is on the wanted list, and you get his ring which you get to keep.\nHe will also drop &lt;a href=\"Razakel%27s%20Hammer\"&gt;Razakel's Hammer&lt;/a&gt; if you had used mindread on &lt;a href=\"Razakel\"&gt;Razakel&lt;/a&gt; back when you were getting the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Tower\"&gt;Battle Tower&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Laiken\"&gt;Laiken&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3201", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3201", "title": "Sinister Motives", "text": "Sinister Motives is a &lt;a href=\"Flames%20of%20Vengeance%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; received from &lt;a href=\"Astridax\"&gt;Astridax&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Lanilor%20Lane\"&gt;Lanilor Lane&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDetailed Walkthrough.\nHe requires three pieces of &lt;a href=\"jewelry\"&gt;jewelry&lt;/a&gt; that belonged to recently deceased people, in order to experiment with rediscovered ancient Orc magic that allows one to enslave souls by binding them to an object. (Explained in the &lt;a href=\"Books%20and%20notes%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; titled \"&lt;a href=\"Writings%20of%20Astridax\"&gt;Writings of Astridax&lt;/a&gt;\".)\nNote: Due to mutually exclusive choices involving the jewelry, doing this quest invalidates &lt;a href=\"Jewellery%20in%20Law\"&gt;Jewellery in Law&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Commitment\"&gt;Eternal Commitment&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Reminiscence%20Of%20The%20Past\"&gt;Reminiscence Of The Past&lt;/a&gt;.\nSub-quest: Earrings for Astridax.\nComplete the quest &lt;a href=\"All%20the%20After%20World%27s%20a%20Stage\"&gt;All the After World's a Stage&lt;/a&gt;, given by &lt;a href=\"Alfred\"&gt;Alfred&lt;/a&gt; at the Aleroth &lt;a href=\"Playhouse\"&gt;Playhouse&lt;/a&gt; to gain entry to the room behind the magical barrier. Speak with Mara's &lt;a href=\"ghost\"&gt;ghost&lt;/a&gt; to receive &lt;a href=\"Mara%27s%20Earrings\"&gt;Mara's Earrings&lt;/a&gt; (if you do not have a dialogue option available to get the earrings, speak with &lt;a href=\"Ransid\"&gt;Ransid&lt;/a&gt; outside &lt;a href=\"Chez%20Chanelle\"&gt;Chez Chanelle&lt;/a&gt; on Lanilor Lane, then return to Mara and ask her about Ransid). Give them to Astridax, who immediately enslaves her soul.\nThis conflicts with the quest &lt;a href=\"Jewellery%20in%20Law\"&gt;Jewellery in Law&lt;/a&gt;, offered by Ransid.\nRewards:\nSub-quest: A Ring for Astridax.\nComplete the quest &lt;a href=\"Bark%20up%20the%20Right%20Tree\"&gt;Bark up the Right Tree&lt;/a&gt; to gain access to &lt;a href=\"Crow%27s%20Nest\"&gt;Crow's Nest&lt;/a&gt;. Enter &lt;a href=\"Decimus%27%20House\"&gt;Decimus' House&lt;/a&gt;, defeat &lt;a href=\"Carmina\"&gt;Carmina&lt;/a&gt; (required for &lt;a href=\"A%20Hunting%20We%20Shall%20Go%20Once%20More\"&gt;A Hunting We Shall Go Once More&lt;/a&gt;), and loot &lt;a href=\"Livia%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Livia's Ring&lt;/a&gt; from small a box. Give it to Astridax, who enslaves Livia's soul.\nThis conflicts with the quest &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Commitment\"&gt;Eternal Commitment&lt;/a&gt;, offered by &lt;a href=\"Decimus\"&gt;Decimus&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Healers%27%20House\"&gt;Healers' House&lt;/a&gt;.\nRewards:\nSub-quest: An Amulet for Astridax.\nComplete the quest &lt;a href=\"Bark%20up%20the%20Right%20Tree\"&gt;Bark up the Right Tree&lt;/a&gt; to gain access to &lt;a href=\"Crow%27s%20Nest\"&gt;Crow's Nest&lt;/a&gt;. Enter &lt;a href=\"Henry%20and%20Eleanor%27s%20House\"&gt;Henry and Eleanor's House&lt;/a&gt; and loot &lt;a href=\"Eleanor%27s%20Necklace\"&gt;Eleanor's Necklace&lt;/a&gt; from a small lockbox in the northwest corner of the house. Give it to Astridax who enslaves Eleanor's soul.\nThis conflicts with the quest &lt;a href=\"Reminiscence%20Of%20The%20Past\"&gt;Reminiscence Of The Past&lt;/a&gt; offered by &lt;a href=\"Ricky\"&gt;Ricky&lt;/a&gt;, the bartender at the &lt;a href=\"Phoenix%20Inn\"&gt;Phoenix Inn&lt;/a&gt;.\nRewards:\nRewards.\nQuest rewards:\nTotal rewards:"}
{"id": "12344", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12344", "title": "Siphon Poison", "text": "Siphon Poison is a &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;master Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive geomancer skill that allows caster to absorb poison surfaces and clouds (of any type) in 8 meter radius and turn them into bonus poison damage for 2 turns as part of the status effect. This damage is applied to the weapons the caster has equipped and as such it is also added to all weapon-based skills (example: &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skill &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Stomp\"&gt;Battle Stomp&lt;/a&gt;). Note that the poison damage bonus gained by the status is applied only on the primary weapon in case caster is wielding two weapons (wands, daggers etc.)\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 1400 gold. Since is a master Geomancer skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 16.\n is one of the few magic-based skills that does not have a scroll.\nSkill Modifiers.\nThe bonus poison damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Geomancer ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. \nNote: The size of cleared poison surfaces and clouds has no effect on the bonus poison damage. Same applies to the type of poison surfaces and clouds as well as their number. The bonus provided by clouds and surfaces does not stack. \nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist poison damage if they have: Poison Immunity Status and high enough Poison Resistance (which lowers poison damage done). Additionally any character that is Undead or has the talent &lt;a href=\"Undead%20%28talent%29\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;, will automatically have + 200 % Poison Resistance which will cause them to heal from all poison damage done.\n properties can be affected by talents and other skills.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Geomancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only &lt;a href=\"Gareth%20Pryce\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; throughout the game on &lt;a href=\"the%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;the Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;, provided their demands are met."}
{"id": "9124", "revid": "35678067", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9124", "title": "Sir Gula's House", "text": "Sir Gula's House is a private residence belonging to the adventurer &lt;a href=\"Gula\"&gt;Gula&lt;/a&gt;. It is located next to the waypoint shrine on &lt;a href=\"Lanilor%20Lane\"&gt;Lanilor Lane&lt;/a&gt;, between &lt;a href=\"Willy%27s%20House\"&gt;Willy's House&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Chez%20Chanelle\"&gt;Chez Chanelle&lt;/a&gt; during the events of \"\". The house has two doors: the front door is locked and guarded by Mieke and Burt, and the back entrance trapdoor is locked as well. Inside, a doorway is boarded up separating the kitchen from the rest of the house. Thus, if entering via the back entrance you cannot access the main area of the house, and if entering via the front door you cannot access the back area (kitchen) of the house.\nDescription.\nBack Entrance.\nTo access the kitchen via the back entrance, &lt;a href=\"mindread\"&gt;mindread&lt;/a&gt; the beggar &lt;a href=\"Darvesh\"&gt;Darvesh&lt;/a&gt; (15000 &lt;a href=\"exp\"&gt;exp&lt;/a&gt;) in the &lt;a href=\"Mardaneus%20Plaza\"&gt;Mardaneus Plaza&lt;/a&gt; district of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;. He knows where the key is hidden, and has been using it periodically to steal &lt;a href=\"Food%20and%20Drinks\"&gt;food&lt;/a&gt; from Gula. This causes the \"Key To Back Entrance\" to spawn on a potted plant right next to the trapdoor (\"6\" on Lanilor Lane map, below).\nInside the small room you'll find a wheel of &lt;a href=\"Gorgombert\"&gt;Gorgombert&lt;/a&gt; cheese on the table (a required for &lt;a href=\"Everybody%27s%20A%20Critic\"&gt;Everybody's A Critic&lt;/a&gt;). You'll also find an unlocked &lt;a href=\"chest\"&gt;chest&lt;/a&gt; along the south wall containing random loot, and some barrels, baskets, and crates that may contain loot.\nGround Floor.\nTo access the main area of the house, you'll need a key to unlock the front door (\"7\" on Lanilor Lane map, below). A copy of \"Gula's key\" is in the possession of his neighbor &lt;a href=\"Alzbeta\"&gt;Alzbeta&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Alzbeta%27s%20Emporium\"&gt;Alzbeta's Emporium&lt;/a&gt;. To obtain it, you need to complete the quest &lt;a href=\"An%20Appetite%20For%20Murder\"&gt;An Appetite For Murder&lt;/a&gt; assigned by &lt;a href=\"Bernard\"&gt;Bernard&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Healers%27%20House\"&gt;Healers' House&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Market\"&gt;Great Market&lt;/a&gt; district. Once complete, the guards will attempt to stop you at the door. The guard Bert can be mindread for 7500 exp, revealing: \"\"{&lt;a href=\"Behrlihn\"&gt;Behrlihn&lt;/a&gt;} There must be some way to gain entry to this place! It is crucial; essential!\"\" Simply tell the guards that you were sent by Alzbeta, and they'll allow you use the key and enter in peace.\nInside you'll find a wheel of &lt;a href=\"Gorgombert\"&gt;Gorgombert&lt;/a&gt; cheese and the \"&lt;a href=\"Encheeseclopedia\"&gt;Encheeseclopedia&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"Books%20and%20notes%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; to the south, on a table under the staircase. There are also a few barrels, baskets, and crates that may contain random loot.\nSecond Floor.\nAtop the stairs you'll find a bedroom to the northeast that has an unlocked &lt;a href=\"chest\"&gt;chest&lt;/a&gt; containing random loot along the north wall. There is also a painting of a &lt;a href=\"pig\"&gt;pig&lt;/a&gt; on the wall, one of several in Gula's house. Southwest of the stairs is a doorway, leading to another staircase where you can ascend to the top floor.\nTop Floor.\nThe large room on the top floor is contains several types of &lt;a href=\"Food%20and%20Drinks\"&gt;food&lt;/a&gt;. Initially you'll find &lt;a href=\"Gula\"&gt;Sir Gula&lt;/a&gt; here, who has been transformed into a &lt;a href=\"troll\"&gt;troll&lt;/a&gt; due to a curse. His insatiable hunger and appalling appearance is making him miserable, so he offers the quest &lt;a href=\"Fat%20Chance\"&gt;Fat Chance&lt;/a&gt; which allows you to remove the curse and return him to his human form.\nWhen you return after completing the quest at &lt;a href=\"Gula%27s%20Archaeological%20Dig\"&gt;Gula's Archaeological Dig&lt;/a&gt;, you'll find that Gula has returned to normal. His desire for exploration and adventure has disappeared, and he gives you a key before leaving the house. The key unlocks Gula's chest in the southwest corner, which contains gold, a &lt;a href=\"Malachite%20Gem\"&gt;Malachite Gem&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Wizard%20Helmet\"&gt;Dragon Wizard Helmet&lt;/a&gt; (part of the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Wizard\"&gt;Dragon Wizard&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"armor%20set\"&gt;armor set&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Gula%27s%20Book\"&gt;Gula's Book&lt;/a&gt; (a quest item required for Clue III of &lt;a href=\"To%20Find%20a%20Wizard\"&gt;To Find a Wizard&lt;/a&gt;), and random loot."}
