{"id": "4450", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4450", "title": "Skeleton", "text": "Skeletons are the reanimated undead, most of which have been resurrected via necormancy. They are commonly found throughout the &lt;a href=\"Aleroth%20catacombs\"&gt;Aleroth catacombs&lt;/a&gt; and elsewhere in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\", although those of a more powerful nature can be found in the &lt;a href=\"cursed%20abbey\"&gt;cursed abbey&lt;/a&gt;, the dark forest &lt;a href=\"Teneb%20Tiriel\"&gt;Teneb Tiriel&lt;/a&gt; and various graveyards and dungeons.\nBiology.\nThe skeletons in the Aleroth Catacombs are formerly living beings which have been transformed into skeletons by the necromancer &lt;a href=\"Thelyron%20Hashnitor\"&gt;Thelyron Hashnitor&lt;/a&gt;, they are destined to wander the catacombs. Waiting for the necromancer's resurrection. If they consider their existence, they will collapse from excess existential thought. Although those under Thelyron's control will collapse after their leader's death, there are others held by other forms of magic who continue to roam such as those at the abbey who are bound by the &lt;a href=\"Engineer\"&gt;Engineer&lt;/a&gt;'s curse.\nSkeletons have an absolute resistance to poison and a minimal resistance to spiritual damage, with exception to conjurers who also have an absolute resistance to spirit. In contrast, they are weak to both fire and lightning damage.\nVariants.\nSkeletal.\nSkeletal warrior.\nSkeletal warriors are the foot soldiers of the undead army, they specialise in closer quarters combat and are armed with clubs.\nOn the first floor of the Aleroth catacombs there is a skeletal warrior with higher than normal stats that can be summoned by lighting the candles surrounding the pentagram.\nSkeletal archer.\nSkeletal archers are the ranged equivalent of the skeletal warrior. Each one is equipped with a bow. In close quarters their only defense is kicking their opponent.\nSkeletal conjurer.\nThe skeletal conjurers, unlike archers and warriors, appear to have been more akin to a dragon or wyvern than a human, since they have boney wings affixed to their back. They can summon skeletal warriors and archers and will attack with their hands in a claw like manner in close combat.\nUpon death, their summoned warriors will remain until killed.\nSkeletal guardian.\nA larger, and visibly armoured version of the skeletal warrior, the skeletal guardian is armed with a dual bladed axe.\nSkeletal lord.\nAs with the skeletal guardian, the skeletal lord is the archer's upgraded counterpart. They wear horned helmets and their arrows are flaming. In addition to this, they have absolute resistance to spiritual damage.\nSkeletal conjurer lord.\nThe skeletal conjurer lord is the stronger variant of the conjurer, unlike its weaker counterpart, it has a reduced resistance to spiritual damage. Conjurer lords also can summon skeleton conjurers, which can also summon normal skeletons.\nSteel.\nSteel variants are encountered in &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Abbey\"&gt;Cursed Abbey&lt;/a&gt;, made by the &lt;a href=\"Engineer\"&gt;Engineer&lt;/a&gt;. They all have a special sound when killed. Their combat tactics resemble those of normal skeletons.\nSteel conjurer.\nThese summon lesser steel skeletons, like archers and warriors.\nInsane.\nInsane variants are found around the forest area in &lt;a href=\"Teneb%20Tiriel\"&gt;Teneb Tiriel&lt;/a&gt;, near the talking tree."}
{"id": "2157", "revid": "90359", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2157", "title": "Skeletons in the Closet", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". \nDetailed Walkthrough.\nEnter the &lt;a href=\"Jackson%27s%20farm\"&gt;Jackson's farm&lt;/a&gt;'s main building and on the rafter to the southwest, above two stacked boxes the key to the basement can be seen. Jump up to the rafter, collect the key and in the southern corner the basement door can be found. Unlock the door and head into the cellar; there is a table at the far end on the right on which &lt;a href=\"Farmer%20Jackson%27s%20diary\"&gt;Farmer Jackson's diary&lt;/a&gt; is place. Pick up the book and read it and the truth about Carl is revealed: he is a jealous husband who murdered &lt;a href=\"Boothe\"&gt;Boothe&lt;/a&gt;, the man Dana was having an affair with.\nFrom here &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Slayer&lt;/a&gt; has two primary choices: confront Carl, or speak to Captain Rodney and show him the evidence of Carl's crimes. If Carl is confronted any option with the exception of bribery will result in the farming attempting to kill the Slayer and he will need to be killed. Demanding a bribe will result in a bribe being paid, however it is still possible to arrange for Rodney to arrest Carl.\nIf the decision instead was made to inform Rodney, head to the &lt;a href=\"barracks\"&gt;barracks&lt;/a&gt; and enter on the ground floor. Rodney can be found in the guards quarters on this level, sat at the bench near the archway to the turret. Speak to him and show him the diary. He will then head to the farm and arrest Carl, imprisoning him in the barrack's jail."}
