{"id": "13514", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13514", "title": "Smiruk", "text": "Smiruk is an &lt;a href=\"orc\"&gt;orc&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Aleroth%20catacombs\"&gt;Aleroth catacombs&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nSmiruk is an orc warrior who has been sent to the catacombs below &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; to retrieve a magical axe known as &lt;a href=\"Slasher\"&gt;Slasher&lt;/a&gt;. He is accompanied by &lt;a href=\"Bregor\"&gt;Bregor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Grim\"&gt;Grim&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Turnak\"&gt;Turnak&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vradnir\"&gt;Vradnir&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Golg\"&gt;Golg&lt;/a&gt; is also in he's company, but further down south."}
{"id": "12273", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12273", "title": "Smoke Cover", "text": "Smoke cloud is a &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; skill in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive mixed skill that allows caster to create a cloud of smoke around themselves in 3 meter radius. The cloud will block vision for all characters effectively hiding them and preventing hostile rangers and spellcasters from attacking singular enemy from afar (unless they are in reach of a skill which affects large enough area). The smoke cloud will disappear after 1 turn.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurgy\"&gt;Aerotheurgy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into both &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Scoundrel\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a any non-source &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Scoundrel\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks are combined. Since is a mixed skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive aerotheurge skill that allows caster to create a cloud of smoke and as such it is not affected by the Level, Aerotheurge ability and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; attribute of the caster.\nHowever the skill itself can still be affected by other skills.\nLocation.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from NPCs in the game. "}
{"id": "17032", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17032", "title": "Smoke Grenade", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"\nCharacteristics.\n is a throwable grenade that deals no damage on its own but creates Smoke Cloud at the area of impact in 3 meter radius. The Smoke Cloud lasts 1 turn.\nAll characters can throw this grenade. However due to the grenade dealing no damage and only creating a cloud it is not possible to increase its effectiveness through abilities or attributes.\nSince is a grenade it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent which decreases the cost of using grenades and scrolls by 1 AP when the secondary hand is free. is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; which increases its range by 5 meters and by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent which increases range by 2 meters.\nCrafting.\nIt is not possible to craft this grenade both in the base game and through the features introduced into the game by Gift Bags.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for."}
