{"id": "2213", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2213", "title": "Borrowed Book", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; issued by &lt;a href=\"Barbatos\"&gt;Barbatos&lt;/a&gt; to upgrade the &lt;a href=\"Alchemy%20Garden\"&gt;Alchemy Garden&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Tower\"&gt;Battle Tower&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDetailed walkthrough.\nBarbatos asks &lt;a href=\"The%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;The Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; to find a book that an old alchemist friend of his once had. The only clue he gives is that the book is located in a cave somewhere in the &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe book is found in the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Cave\"&gt;Dark Cave&lt;/a&gt;, which is found on the southern cliffside from the Grand Knight shrine in Orobas Fjords. The entrance is located east of the &lt;a href=\"Camp%20Eagle%27s%20Nest\"&gt;Camp Eagle's Nest&lt;/a&gt; teleporter.\nNear the entrance, is a fight with the bandits, of which &lt;a href=\"Suja\"&gt;Suja&lt;/a&gt; is carrying a key to open the gate.\nFollow the path to the east and up the stairwell. At the end of the chamber, are four pressure pads, which must be activated in the correct order to release the barrier to the western chamber. Each pad will begin to glow when activated in the correct order, however if an incorrect pad is activated, the sequence resets. The correct sequence is to activate the second closest pad to the chests, then furthest from the chests, the closest to the chests and then second furthest from the chests.\nOnce the barrier has been dispelled, head west back through the cave to opposite end on the passage and down the stairs. In this room &lt;a href=\"Ragon\"&gt;Ragon&lt;/a&gt;, (who is also a target for &lt;a href=\"A%20Hunting%20We%20Shall%20Go%20Again\"&gt;A Hunting We Shall Go Again&lt;/a&gt;) can be found with a handful of bandits. Defeat him to go deeper into the chamber. One will find three golden dragon statues, one either side of the passageway and the third upon ledge on the eastern side. Rotate each statue until the can be rotated no further, then pass the statues to find the book and a gold pouch on the ground. \nReturn to the battle tower and give the book to Barbatos who will advise the platform is ready to be upgrade. The quest will conclude at this stage, however, &lt;a href=\"Sassan\"&gt;Sassan&lt;/a&gt; must be spoken to to upgrade the platform."}
