{"id": "10049", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10049", "title": "Bow (DOS EE)", "text": "General.\nThe Bow ability is generally used by &lt;a href=\"Bow%20Ranger%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;Bow Rangers&lt;/a&gt; who maximize the use of their &lt;a href=\"Expert%20Marksman%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;Expert Marksman&lt;/a&gt; skills.\nIn DOS EE, the Bow skill differs much more from the Crossbow skill. The Bow skill directly increases the damage of bows, which allows for more powerful Expert Marksman skills. This is because Expert Marksman skills' damage is based on the damage of the weapon equipped. Unlike skills, Expert Marksman skills cannot crit, which means bows are the superior weapon. Bow Rangers want to max their to reduce cooldowns on their Expert Marksman abilities. On the other hand, &lt;a href=\"Crossbow%20Rangers%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;Crossbow Rangers&lt;/a&gt; mainly auto-attack and only increase their dexterity to meet gear requirements."}
{"id": "5590", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5590", "title": "Bow (Original Sin)", "text": "Bow increases a character's damage rating with bow weapons (this does not include &lt;a href=\"Crossbow%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;).\nBows use a large amount of action points to attack with each turn (generally 3 to 4), so a high Speed stat or the talent is recommended. Furthermore, a far away target will have a lower chance to hit. Even though the Perception stat increases accuracy over long distances as well as increase critical hit chance, the Dexterity stat increases damage and accuracy much more significantly.\nAttributes that affect bows.\nEvery 0.2 meters reduces chance to hit by 1%\nEach point of increases the distance before penalties due to range take effect by 0.4 meters and critical hit chance by 2%.\nEach point of increases chance to hit by 6% and offense rating by 6 (when using a bow)."}
