{"id": "8503", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8503", "title": "Broken Valley Mine Tower", "text": "Broken Valley Mine Tower is a &lt;a href=\"Locations%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;location&lt;/a&gt; accessible while in &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Form\"&gt;dragon form&lt;/a&gt; after &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Damian's&lt;/a&gt; army invades the &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt;. It is located in the south-central area of the valley, southeast from &lt;a href=\"Lovis%27%20Tower\"&gt;Lovis' Tower&lt;/a&gt;, and northwest of &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley%20Mine\"&gt;Broken Valley Mine&lt;/a&gt; (see map below).\nUpon entering the tower, a conversation is overheard between two &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; members, Scroud and Siddell. They notice you, so take them out quickly. Once they have been disposed of, it is time to loot your way up the tower. On the ground floor you'll find three chests, two of which are locked but can be &lt;a href=\"Lockpick%20%28Divinity%20II%29\"&gt;lockpick&lt;/a&gt;ed. Up a short flight of stairs to a wooden platform with winches you'll find two more unlocked chests. Proceed up to the next floor, where you'll find four more chests, and a small box under the stairs. Some of the chests can be lockpicked, but one requires a key. They all contain random loot.\nAt the top of the next flight of stairs you'll encounter &lt;a href=\"Williams\"&gt;Williams&lt;/a&gt;, Tanya, and Brent. Williams will provide you with a key to the Broken Valley Mine that is needed for the quest &lt;a href=\"Lock%20and%20Key\"&gt;Lock and Key&lt;/a&gt;, and he can be &lt;a href=\"mindread\"&gt;mindread&lt;/a&gt; to learn about a treasure chest in the mine office. You'll automatically begin the quest &lt;a href=\"A%20Guild%20Without%20a%20Master\"&gt;A Guild Without a Master&lt;/a&gt; at the end of your conversation. Simply escort him to the ground floor of the tower unharmed, fending off the invading Black Ring members as you go, to complete the quest.\nReturn to the top floor and pick up the key from an alchemy table, it opens the locked chest on the floor below. Loot it, and you've done all there is to do at this location.\nMap.\nLocation of Broken Valley Mine Tower:"}
{"id": "2138", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2138", "title": "Broken Valley Village", "text": " is a village in the north-westernmost part of &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nBuilt back when the region was still known as Valley of the Shrines, the village was built to be self sustaining. Initially consisting of the &lt;a href=\"barracks\"&gt;barracks&lt;/a&gt;, the perimeter wall short followed and in place, the rest of the village fell into place. The village's design fails to be absolutely self-sustaining as grain must be brought in from &lt;a href=\"Jackson%27s%20farm\"&gt;Jackson's farm&lt;/a&gt; for processing in the &lt;a href=\"watermill\"&gt;watermill&lt;/a&gt;.\nA haven for both the good and the wicked alike, the village in &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt; is a surprisingly peaceful place to visit, especially given its role in the ancient struggles between &lt;a href=\"Human\"&gt;Human&lt;/a&gt; and dragon kind. Many travelling merchants call this place their home, and naturally that also attracts a good number of &lt;a href=\"bandits\"&gt;bandits&lt;/a&gt;, looking out for fresh, heavy purses to rob. \nThe local guards have a powerful reputation for their lack of tolerance with thieves in particular, and so despite having to still keep eyes open for opportunistic trouble, Broken Valley Village is a relatively safe place to spend time.\nFollowing the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt;'s acquisition of the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Tower\"&gt;Battle Tower&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Damian&lt;/a&gt; decimates the area, destroying the village.\nLayout.\nUpon reaching the village entrance, &lt;a href=\"Paul\"&gt;Paul&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Joris\"&gt;Joris&lt;/a&gt; can be found either side of entry. Passing through, the area opens out into the broad streets with several &lt;a href=\"New%20Order\"&gt;New Order&lt;/a&gt; guards patrolling. To the right a short ramp up to the &lt;a href=\"barracks\"&gt;barracks&lt;/a&gt; entrance can seen, alternatively the barracks can also be accessed by taking the stairs either side of the entrance onto the ramparts and turning left, taking the door directly ahead or climbing the spiral ramp then turning right to enter the upper turret. On the ramparts themselves &lt;a href=\"Keane\"&gt;Keane&lt;/a&gt; is patrolling to the left of the stairs and &lt;a href=\"Wellesly\"&gt;Wellesly&lt;/a&gt; to the right.\nReturning back down to the street and following the path it forks left and right, the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Boar\"&gt;Black Boar&lt;/a&gt; can be seen on the left with &lt;a href=\"Stan\"&gt;Stan&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ollie\"&gt;Ollie&lt;/a&gt; sat on the table outside of the doorway; the right path goes under the bridge to the barracks and forks again just past the bridge, the left leading to the New Order training; &lt;a href=\"Monica\"&gt;Monica&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hans\"&gt;Hans&lt;/a&gt; can be found patrolling this section and three training guards being supervised by the drill sergeant are in the training area itself. In the southeast of the training area is a doorway to the &lt;a href=\"watermill\"&gt;watermill&lt;/a&gt;, which &lt;a href=\"Winthrop\"&gt;Winthrop&lt;/a&gt; is guarding and the northwest another stairway leading up the ramparts here; &lt;a href=\"Sean\"&gt;Sean&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Phoebe\"&gt;Phoebe&lt;/a&gt; are patrolling this section. Climbing the stairs to the ramparts and looking northeast there is the final door to the barracks.\nCrossing either through the stream or over the ramparts, the blacksmith built against &lt;a href=\"Derk%27s%20house\"&gt;Derk's house&lt;/a&gt; can be found. Derk can be found here, with exception of if he is meeting &lt;a href=\"Dana%20Jackson\"&gt;Dana Jackson&lt;/a&gt;. on the path in front of the blacksmiths &lt;a href=\"Richard\"&gt;Richard&lt;/a&gt; can be found patrolling from the ramparts up to &lt;a href=\"Folo%27s%20house\"&gt;Folo's house&lt;/a&gt; as well as &lt;a href=\"Rachel\"&gt;Rachel&lt;/a&gt; who patrols up. To the right of Folo's house is the animal pen, which is locked, but can be accessed by either jumping the fence or walking through his house; in the pen itself is &lt;a href=\"Folo\"&gt;Folo&lt;/a&gt; and a single chicken. Continuing to follow the path round, the &lt;a href=\"chapel\"&gt;chapel&lt;/a&gt; and graveyard can be seen on the left, where &lt;a href=\"Romon\"&gt;Romon&lt;/a&gt;, and two New Order guards, &lt;a href=\"Jeffrey\"&gt;Jeffrey&lt;/a&gt; (who will patrol down to the blacksmith) and &lt;a href=\"Arnold\"&gt;Arnold&lt;/a&gt; can be found. To the rear of the chapel on the southeast side is a chest that can be unlocked.\nReturning from the rear of the chapel there are two bridges across the stream. The furthest bridge leads to the wash line where the gossipers &lt;a href=\"Peggy\"&gt;Peggy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sue\"&gt;Sue&lt;/a&gt; can be found, there is also the path back down to the barracks to the right of the line; it is also possible to follow the embankment to the closet bridge where &lt;a href=\"Lamotte\"&gt;Lamotte&lt;/a&gt; and his stand can be found. Passing Lamotte's stand the path forks again, left leading to the bridge over to the barracks upper entrance and the spiral ramp back down to the lower level and entrance or almost directly ahead to &lt;a href=\"Locke%27s%20Cart\"&gt;Locke's Cart&lt;/a&gt;. To the right of the cart, &lt;a href=\"Furley\"&gt;Furley&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Namdar\"&gt;Namdar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Nightwinkle\"&gt;Nightwinkle&lt;/a&gt; can be found standing in a circle if they were rescued from their slumber in &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt;. Heading left leads back down to the Black Boar, &lt;a href=\"Tim\"&gt;Tim&lt;/a&gt;'s barn can be found just before reaching the Black Boar and within it Derk's key can be found if he was mindread. &lt;a href=\"Elisabeth\"&gt;Elisabeth&lt;/a&gt; can be found patrolling this area, possibly being tailed by a lovestruck &lt;a href=\"Lomax\"&gt;Lomax&lt;/a&gt; if he was told she missed him."}
