{"id": "16555", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16555", "title": "Burning (Status)", "text": "Burning is a &lt;a href=\"status%20effect\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in ' and '.\nDivinity: Original Sin.\nEffects.\nDeals [X-Y] &lt;a href=\"fire%20damage\"&gt;fire damage&lt;/a&gt; every turn.\nDivinity: Original Sin II.\nDescription.\nBurning is a negative environmental &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; which inflicts fire damage upon afflicted character. Fire damage will gradually destroy Magic Armour until it reaches 0 when it will start to damage Vitality and stay on the character independent of environment. While Burning is a negative status it is also the only way to remove Enwebbed status effect (the other being &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Legs\"&gt;Spider Legs&lt;/a&gt; spell).\nBurning will also lower Fire Resistance by 15 % and increase Water Resistance by 10 %.\nCause.\nThere are many ways through which burning status effect can be triggered. On &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; it is the contact with \"fire surface\" or \"fire cloud\". These can be caused by igniting \"poison\" or \"oil\" surfaces and clouds. \nIn combat Burning can be caused by myriad of items or most commonly &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; spells. \nTreatment.\nSince Burning is a status effect tied to fire it can be resolved through opposite water element which is tied to &lt;a href=\"Wet%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Wet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chilled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Chilled&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Permafrost%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Permafrost&lt;/a&gt; status effects. Additionaly Burning can be removed by &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Fire%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Holy Fire&lt;/a&gt; status which will also grant immunity to it. If there are no viable means of reverting the status, then the best way to avoid damage to Vitality is by keeping Magic armour above 0. All consumable items that restore Magic armour can be strengthened by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "6031", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6031", "title": "Burning Blaze", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Pyrokinetic spell&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". \nDescription.\nCast 2 projectiles of magical fire that deals X-Y fire damage. \n50% base chance to set \nCan target terrain to create fire surface, burn ooze, evaporate water or melt ice.\nLocation.\nThe Burning Blaze skill book can be bought from merchants. The scroll version of the spell \"is\" sold by merchants, but is called Flare (level 9)."}
