{"id": "20246", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20246", "title": "Charmed (Status)", "text": "Necrofire is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nCharmed is a status effect that can be both beneficial and harmful, depending on who is afflicted. Charmed will make afflicted character temporarily ally with the one that charmed them. The usual duration of this effect is for 2 turns. \nCause.\nThere are only few spells and items that may cause this effect, but only if target character has no Magic armour. If they have Magic armour above 0 they will resist being Charmed. The only exception is character with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Glass Cannon talent&lt;/a&gt; who will be afflicted by it regardless of their armour values.\nNotable NPCs.\nFollowing NPCs will use spells or items that cause this status effect:\nTreatment.\nThe only way to remove the Charmed effect is by either by having immunity to its influence, keeping Magic armour above 0 or use Mind affecting spells and items that will cancel charmed status effect. Charmed is generally negated by &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Clear-Minded%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Clear-Minded&lt;/a&gt; status effects but other status effects such as &lt;a href=\"Permafrost%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Permafrost&lt;/a&gt; will also work.\nStatus negation.\nFollowing spells will completely cancel out Charmed when casted."}
{"id": "17015", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17015", "title": "Charming Arrow", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a special arrow which deals no damage and inflicts &lt;a href=\"Charmed%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Charmed Status&lt;/a&gt; (1 Turn) if the Magic Armour of affected characters reaches 0.\nDue to this arrow dealing no damage on its own it is not possible to increase its damage output through stats or height difference.\nSince is a special arrow it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Arrow Recovery&lt;/a&gt; talent which grants 33 % chance to recover a special arrow after firing it. This arrow is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Elemental Ranger&lt;/a&gt; talent that grants additional elemental damage bonus depending on the surface the shooting character is standing in. It is possible to increase the range of the arrow by 2 meters through the &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent."}
