{"id": "3371", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3371", "title": "Child of the Chaos", "text": "Child of the Chaos is the second novella in the \"Divinity\" &lt;a href=\"series\"&gt;series&lt;/a&gt; by Rhianna Pratchett. The story precursors the events of \"&lt;a href=\"Beyond%20Divinity\"&gt;Beyond Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nStory.\nFollowing the defeat of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; in 1218 AD and the recovery of the baby &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Damian&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt;, \"Child of the Chaos\" tells of the upbringing of Damian under the divine's care. Even as a baby, Damian is able to wield the powers of &lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt; and as he grows, his power does.\nAs a teenager, Damian becomes a part of the &lt;a href=\"Paladins\"&gt;Paladins&lt;/a&gt;, freeing Lucian to investigate Black Ring sightings. During these years, the gods begin to meddle in mortal affairs, leading Lucian to the rift temple and through the rifts to other dimensions, including modern-day earth. Damian also meets &lt;a href=\"Ygerna\"&gt;Ygerna&lt;/a&gt; as seemingly unassuming witch, who is in fact the daughter of a Black Ring necromancer, who was executed by the Divine and his paladins.\nWorking for the Ring, Ygerna reveals some of the power within Damian; events during their relationship reveal her true intentions to Lucian, who summarily executes her after interrogation. Damian, seeing her execution by accident, turns against the divine and joins the Ring as their leader.\nDuring a showdown between Lucian and Damian at the rift temple, Damian is sealed within &lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;, his memory erased. Taken in by the &lt;a href=\"Raanaar\"&gt;Raanaar&lt;/a&gt;, who attempt to return him to the realm from which he came, Damian slowly recovers his memories (but does not reveal this to his hosts). Unable to return him, the elder travels through to Rivellon and discovers the truth behind Damian.\nWhilst the elder is journeying, Damian steals the protective shield of the Raan from their temple, enabling the &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic realm to enter Raan lands once more. After a bitter battle, of which the Raan are constantly on the losing end, &lt;a href=\"Asmodheus\"&gt;Asmodheus&lt;/a&gt; finally ends the battle, taking the elder's daughter as his slave and Nemesis as his realm. Damian's location remains unknown at the end of the story.\nCanon contradictions.\nFollowing the release of \"\" the novella has fallen out of line with the official &lt;a href=\"Larian%20Studios\"&gt;Larian Studios&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"timeline\"&gt;timeline&lt;/a&gt;. In the novella, &lt;a href=\"Zandalor\"&gt;Zandalor&lt;/a&gt; aided Lucian in wielding his powers, however, in \"Original Sin II\" he received tutor ledge at &lt;a href=\"the%20Academy%20of%20the%20Seven\"&gt;the Academy of the Seven&lt;/a&gt; from the tutors who taught Godwoken there. Furthermore, Lucian has a second son, &lt;a href=\"Alexandar\"&gt;Alexandar&lt;/a&gt; who grew up with Damian. This second child is not referenced at all in the novella, however, this does not necessarily mean the events as a whole could not have happened as written; the story focuses on events directly related to Lucian and Damian and is told from a perception outside of the character's view and focuses solely on key events relating to Damian."}
{"id": "15505", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15505", "title": "Children of the Night", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20books%20and%20notes\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "20220", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20220", "title": "Chilled (Status)", "text": "Chilled is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". \nDescription.\nChilled is a negative environmental status effect that is associated with lowered temperature and may lead to &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt; if untreated. Chilled on its own lowers character Movement Speed by 35 % and Dodging by 30 %. Furthermore Chilled status lowers Water Resistance by 20 % and Air Resistance by 10 %. However it increases Fire Resistance by 10 %. \nCause.\nChilled is a water based status effect which can be caused by many ways and is applied only if Magic armour is at 0. Note that there are few places on &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; where environment itself may freeze characters such as &lt;a href=\"Arx%20Harbour\"&gt;Arx Harbour&lt;/a&gt; cellar flooded with freezing water or proximity to &lt;a href=\"Slane\"&gt;Winter Dragon&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Beach\"&gt;Dragon's Beach&lt;/a&gt; regardless of Magic armour being above 0.\nIn combat Chilled can be inflicted by casting certain &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; spells or using certain items. \nNotable NPCs.\nFollowing NPCs are characters which may utilise spells or items that will afflict their enemies with Chilled status.\nTreatment.\nChilled is a status that is based on water and damages Magic armour, therefore it can be negated via fire based tools and spells or resisted through increasing Magic armour. On &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; Chilled status will be negated via fire surface or fire cloud or by simply being in proximity of source of warmth such as lava, campfire or &lt;a href=\"Firelamp\"&gt;Firelamp&lt;/a&gt; which will set &lt;a href=\"Warm%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Warm&lt;/a&gt; status.\nMagic armour restoration.\nMagic armour can be increased via blessed ice surface, items or through spells. Notable status effect that is associated with increased Magic armour is &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Shell%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Magic shell&lt;/a&gt;.\nStatus negation.\nAs mentioned above the easiest way to utterly remove Chilled is through fire based status effects such as &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt; or Warm. Other status effect that directly removes Chilled is &lt;a href=\"Blessed%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Blessed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Permafrost%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Permafrost&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "10439", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10439", "title": "Chloroform", "text": "Chloroform is a &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nDestroys magic armour and then tries to set Sleeping.\nDoes not break Invisibility or Sneaking.\nDamage scales off level and Finesse.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Scoundrel\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. Since is a starter Scoundrel skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Scoundrel skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well.\nSince is a weapon based skill and as such it does not have a scroll. It is also not possible to craft a skillbook.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell scoundrel skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell."}
