{"id": "5078", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5078", "title": "Cleric (Original Sin)", "text": "The cleric is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%20Classes\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt; in ' and the '.\nBackground.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Seven%20Gods\"&gt;Seven Gods&lt;/a&gt; may be almighty, but they hardly expect to fight their own wars. Thus an order of ascetics devoted to the Seven Gods and practiced in the arts of war and healing carries out the will of the divine.\nThese men and women are trained to transform a spartan diet of crickets and snow into the raw strength necessary to turn the tide in any holy war. They restore and regenerate their allies as thoroughly as they annihilate their foes.\nEnemies of the &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; and all unrighteous magic, Clerics are the cleansing hand of the gods made manifest. For centuries, Clerics have worked alongside the &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Source%20Hunters\"&gt;Order of the Source Hunters&lt;/a&gt; to purify the land of evil magic.\nStarting statistics.\nFollowing table shows all statistics, spells and items of the Cleric at the start of the game. There are no major differences between \"Classic\" and \"Enhanced\" versions of the game save for few minor changes in skills and items at their disposal. \nIn \"Enhanced Edition\" the Clerics original hydrosophist spell &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Heal\"&gt;Minor Heal&lt;/a&gt; has been replaced with &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;Regeneration&lt;/a&gt;. In addition to this the Cleric has in \"Enhanced Edition\" a &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Hand%20Grenade\"&gt;Holy Hand Grenade&lt;/a&gt; in their inventory."}
{"id": "10587", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10587", "title": "Cleric (Original Sin 2)", "text": "The Cleric is a &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;mage class&lt;/a&gt; of physical prowess and magical support in \"\".\nSummary.\nThe Cleric is a mage, who harnesses the powers of &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt; to decimate their enemies and heal their allies. Their primary weapons are a one-handed mace, axe or sword and a shield. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. Their combat abilities are further supported by their innate talent &lt;a href=\"Talents%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hot Head&lt;/a&gt; which increases their critical chance by +10% critical chance as well as their accurancy by + 10%. This talent works however only when they are at their maximum Vitality. \nThe cleric starts with &lt;a href=\"Decaying%20Touch%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Decaying Touch&lt;/a&gt; which is a necromancer skill, dealing physical damage up close and applying decay if the target does not have \"physical armour\". Second starting necromancer skill is the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Sucker%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Blood Sucker&lt;/a&gt; which allows its user to absorb the blood surface on which they stand in order to heal themselves. The last skill clerics have from start is the hydrosophist skill &lt;a href=\"Restoration%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Restoration&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to heal themselves and their allies. \nOutside combat they may utilise their &lt;a href=\"Bartering%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Bartering&lt;/a&gt; civil skill in order to make their dealings with traders easier. \nMercenary Myrella.\nMyrella is an &lt;a href=\"Elves\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be &lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Recruiting%20Mercenaries\"&gt;hired&lt;/a&gt; from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. Her role on the battlefield is that of cleric, a healer and mage who can support their allies through &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; magic. \nDetailed Description.\nOverview.\nCleric is a hybrid class that specialises in dealing physical damage or water damage and therefore can damage both physical and magic armour of their enemies. \nPhysical damage relies on &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; attribute which boosts damage done by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; spells. Water damage relies on &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; attribute which boosts damage done by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; spells. Note that out of these two, only Hydrosophist combat ability increases damage done. Necromancer ability only increases health received by dealing direct damage to Vitality of your enemies. Should you decide to go for Necromancer spells, therefore physical damage, as your main offensive ability it is crucial to invest points in &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; combat ability. Therefore damage-wise should you decide to focus on necromancy, it may be best to change class to &lt;a href=\"Inquisitor%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Inquisitor&lt;/a&gt; whose secondary combat ability alongside Necromancer is Warfare.\nIt should be noted however that relying to heavily on water damage leaves one vulnerable to enemies with high Water Resistance. There are very few enemies across the game with resistance to Physical damage, however that does not mean they do not exist.\nIn regards to equipment they may wear either Heavy Armour (high Physical Armour / low Magic Armour) and Cloth Armour (low Physical Armour / High Magic Armour) as these require points in either Strength or Intelligence.\nList of all skills available.\nCleric is a class focused on casting &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophy\"&gt;Hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Necromancy\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; spells. Both of these are capable of healing the caster and support their allies. Hydrosophy is focused on powers of water that allow Cleric to restore Magic Armour, summon rain and freeze their opponents. Necromancy allows Cleric to resurrect corpses of the fallen as their temporary minions, curse their enemies and leech their health. \nFollowing table shows all spells which Cleric can learn as they level up and invest points in respective combat abilities."}
