{"id": "12340", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12340", "title": "Living Wall", "text": "Living wall is a &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;master Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive geomancer skill that allows caster to summon poison emitting vine wall for 2 turns anywhere in 13 meter radius from the caster. The vine wall can extend up to 7 meters. The vine wall creates a poison clouds that extend up to 2 meter radius. The clouds will do poison damage to all characters. The vines have no Physical Armour or Magic Armour.\nCharacters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 2 turns and suffer damage directly to their health, with the exception of &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; who will receive &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status effect regardless of their armour values and restore their health in proportion to the poison damage dealt by the status.\nThe vines have the following resistance values:\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is not reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 1400 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Earth%20Skillbook\"&gt;High Tier Blank Earth Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a master Geomancer skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 16.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 350 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a offensive Geomancer skill that conjures a wall of vines that create poison clouds. As such they alone deal no damage and cast no skill. Because of this it is not possible to improve them as their stats (Vitality) rely solely on the Level of the caster.\nHowever the skill itself can be affected by other skills and talents.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Geomancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only &lt;a href=\"Gareth%20Pryce\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; throughout the game on &lt;a href=\"the%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;the Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;, provided their demands are met."}
{"id": "12376", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12376", "title": "Living on the Edge", "text": " is an &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;adept Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive necromancer skill that allows caster to bless target character (in 13 meter range) and thus keep them alive against all odds by preventing their Vitality to go below 1 point. The skill applies Death Resist status effect which is a positive status effect and as such bypasses all armour. Should the target character be a summoned entity, their lifetime will be prolonged for the duration of the skill.\nThe Death Resist status effect will not allow the Vitality of afflicted character to go below 1 point at all circumstances. This include damage from Deathfog clouds, Lava surfaces, attacks from &lt;a href=\"Shrieker\"&gt;Shrieker&lt;/a&gt;s and some other skills which are listed below and do not rely on character annihilating themselves (example: &lt;a href=\"Vile%20Burst\"&gt;Vile Burst&lt;/a&gt; skill of &lt;a href=\"Raise%20Bloated%20Corpse\"&gt;Bloated Corpse&lt;/a&gt; or effects of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;summoning&lt;/a&gt; skill &lt;a href=\"Supercharger\"&gt;Supercharger&lt;/a&gt;).\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Necromancy\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Necromancy%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Necromancy Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is an adept Necromancer skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 9.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 260 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive skill that prevents death of a character under its effects for 2 turns and as such this bonus cannot be modified.\nHowever skill itself can be modified through talents and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell necromancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only \"&lt;a href=\"Tarquin\"&gt;Tarquin&lt;/a&gt;\" is guaranteed to follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; as they travel with &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;. \"&lt;a href=\"Jahan\"&gt;Jahan&lt;/a&gt;\" may join the Godwoken on the ship as well if his demands are met. "}
