{"id": "10284", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10284", "title": "Lizards", "text": "Lizards are one of the seven sentient &lt;a href=\"Race\"&gt;races&lt;/a&gt; who inhabit &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;.\nPhysiology.\nTall and lean with good constitution lizards spend most of their life time taking care of their bodies, carefully implementing a rigid sport and nutrition regime improving their physical and mental prowess bringing their person to its pinnacle. Their height ranges from 6 to nearly 7 feet and weight between 130 and 230 pounds.\nLizards are cold-blooded and born from eggs. It should be noted however that any comparison to snakes, toads and turtles is regarded as a great offense and is met with swift retribution as lizards believe they are descended from &lt;a href=\"Dragon\"&gt;Ancient dragons&lt;/a&gt; themselves.\nCulture.\nGoverment.\nLizards have an empire ruled by three houses: &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20War\"&gt;House of War&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Law\"&gt;House of Law&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Dreams\"&gt;House of Dreams&lt;/a&gt; . The empire in turn is ruled by an heir from House of War royal bloodline.\nReligion.\nLizards mainly worship their creator Seven God &lt;a href=\"Zorl-Stissa\"&gt;Zorl-Stissa&lt;/a&gt; to whom they pay tribute with their feats be they from war or other area as Zorl-Stissa values perfection. Lizards also pay tribute to&lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;the Divine One&lt;/a&gt; since he is regarded as an Avatar of all of &lt;a href=\"the%20Seven%20Gods\"&gt;the Seven Gods&lt;/a&gt; .\nFamily.\nFamily is the primary unit in the Ancient Empire and is mainly regarded as a means of continuing and preserving each of the progenitors lineage. This means that when comes the time for a lizard to choose a partner they mainly judge qualities as position, fitness, attractiveness, intelligence and diplomacy. Love in the Ancient Empire is mostly considered as a bonus.\nThis implies that any physical, mental or emotional handicaps are considered as extremely shameful and some extremist parents would go so far as to murder their child rather than have their bloodline polluted with imperfection. The ideal of perfection begins with blood and extends to all of the family aspects as parents push their children to excell in all areas of life, especially in sports, intelligence and social activities. Lizards are also highly competitive as there can be only one on top. This leads to high profile or bloody rivalries which can get solved either by the House of Law or the House of War\nThanks to the ideal of perfection the Ancient Empire has some of the finest athletes, warriors, scholars and artists across Rivellon but at the same time produces the highest number of exile and disinherited castaways.\nNotable Lizards.\n\"Original Sin 2\".\nIn you can play as either custom female or male lizard or as &lt;a href=\"the%20Red%20Prince\"&gt;the Red Prince&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Divinity Original Sin: The Board Game\".\nIn \"\" you can play as Red Prince or &lt;a href=\"Farzanah\"&gt;Farzanah&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Divinity Fallen Heroes\".\nIn the player can have the Red Prince (Emperor) in their party during mission or other unnamed lizard &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "17864", "revid": "46132361", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17864", "title": "Lizards (Divine Divinity)", "text": "Lizards in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\" are largely hostile to the other races, and reside in damp or humid areas. There is only one friendly lizard that &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; will encounter: &lt;a href=\"Goemoe\"&gt;Goemoe&lt;/a&gt;, a healer in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;, who later becomes the representative of lizard race to the &lt;a href=\"Council%20of%20Seven\"&gt;Council of Seven&lt;/a&gt;. Most lizards are resistant to &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Damage\"&gt;Poison Damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nVariants.\nDragon Assassin.\nVariant of &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Assassin\"&gt;Lizard Assassin&lt;/a&gt;, found in &lt;a href=\"Teneb%20Tiriel\"&gt;Teneb Tiriel&lt;/a&gt;.\nDragon Fanatic.\nVariant of &lt;a href=\"Fanatic%20Lizard\"&gt;Fanatic Lizard&lt;/a&gt;, found in &lt;a href=\"Teneb%20Tiriel\"&gt;Teneb Tiriel&lt;/a&gt;.\nDragon Warrior.\nVariant of &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Warrior\"&gt;Lizard Warrior&lt;/a&gt;, found in &lt;a href=\"Teneb%20Tiriel\"&gt;Teneb Tiriel&lt;/a&gt;.\nLizard Assassin.\nLizard assassins are primary long range fighters, but in a pinch they will use poisoned attacks at close range.\nLizard Warrior.\nLizard warriors are close range combatants that use a double ended pole staff to attack their targets.\nFanatic Lizard.\nFanatic lizards utilise explosives at close or long range, with little regard for themselves. Aside from the normal resistance to poison, fanatics are also immune to spiritual damage.\nLizard Mage.\nLizard mages use &lt;a href=\"Meteorstrike\"&gt;Meteorstrike&lt;/a&gt; to smite their opponents as well as &lt;a href=\"Withering%20Curse\"&gt;Withering Curse&lt;/a&gt;.\nLightning Lizard.\nA more powerful warrior, that use an electrically charged pole staff to attack their opponents. They also resist lightning damage, rending them free from harm wielding their own weapon.\nLizard Archmage.\nThe most senior mage of the lizard race. Alongside Meteorstrike, archmage's can also use &lt;a href=\"Withering%20Curse\"&gt;Withering Curse&lt;/a&gt; against their targets."}
