{"id": "4184", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4184", "title": "Lost Cavern", "text": "The Lost Cavern is a &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis%20locations\"&gt;small cave&lt;/a&gt; by the Chapel Waypoint Shrine that consists of few chests and some minor loot in \"\".\nLayout.\nUpon entering the cavern, head down the stairs where 2 tribal goblins and a chest can be seen. Continuing past there is a tribal goblin warrior, shaman and chief. By the fire to left there is a chair with a key on to of it; this is required to explore deeper in the cavern. The path then veers right where two more warriors and a healer can be seen at the far end. Before the path then veers right again there is a droxelite ore vein and &lt;a href=\"whisperwood\"&gt;whisperwood&lt;/a&gt;, then two more warriors will attempt to take down the Slayer further up the path. The cavern will then change from natural rock to stonework with stone skulls emblazoning the walls. Head down the stairs which spiral 180\u00b0 left. \nAt the bottom of the stairwell is a corridor with a locked gate, which requires the key from earlier to open. Unlock the gate and within is a storage room with two barrels immediately infront. Turn left and there will be two chests, the one on the left contains the &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Dwellers%20Helmet\"&gt;Wild Dwellers Helmet&lt;/a&gt;. Turn right and a desk can be seen with &lt;a href=\"Elvish%20Tales\"&gt;Elvish Tales&lt;/a&gt; sat atop it. Turning right again will lead back to barrels; go past them and stand in front of the throne, a box appear containing &lt;a href=\"Amulet%20of%20Slantwig\"&gt;Amulet of Slantwig&lt;/a&gt;. Turn right again to find another chest."}
