{"id": "2285", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2285", "title": "Lovis", "text": "Lord Lovis is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; and bound to his &lt;a href=\"Lovis%27%20Tower\"&gt;tower&lt;/a&gt; and approached by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nThe only child of &lt;a href=\"Anastas\"&gt;Anastas&lt;/a&gt;, a queen of the ancient Kingdom of &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt;. At some point he became a disciple of &lt;a href=\"Maxos\"&gt;Maxos&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen he was 17 years old, he and &lt;a href=\"Amdusias\"&gt;Amdusias&lt;/a&gt; attempted to use spells too powerful for them. As a result a fire storm destroyed a town, while killing hundreds in its wake. \nEnraged Maxos decreed that only one of them will become a Dragon Knight. Eversince he and Amdusias became bitter rivals in a race which Lovis had ultimately won.\nDuring his days as a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; he had done many deeds. These include winning a duel with a Dragon Knight Bronn, by biting off his head, in the skies above &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt;. His most famous feat however was during The Battle of Ten Thousand in which he slew more than six hundred foes and three &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; generals.\nWhile his fame was great and noble goals earned him admiration from his students his attitude and his priorities began to decline with time. Duty was replaced by sloth, his watch over the valley replaced with wine and feminine distractions. With time Lovis became cruel and feared. This reached its peak when arch-&lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ba%27al\"&gt;Ba'al&lt;/a&gt; raided Broken Valley.\nFor failure to protect the valley he was punished by Maxos, who ripped his soul and bound it into a stone, which he placed within his temple.\nLovis haunted his tower for over a millenia, until &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; approached him in 1300 AD. While giving the Knight the key to enter the Maxos Temple he asked whether the Knight could retrieve his soul from the hands of his rival Amdusias.\nWhether the Knight returned his soul to him or not remains a mystery. "}
