{"id": "5586", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5586", "title": "Man-at-Arms (Original Sin)", "text": "The Man-at-Arms school focuses on enhancing physical damage and defense as well as disabling enemies through crowd control such as . However, every character should consider a one level dip for access to one of the strongest heals in the game, Cure Wounds, a free self teleport with Battering Ram, and the only knock down removal in game, Helping Hand. In the late game, Man-at-Arms offers some strong AoE buffs like Inspire and debuffs like Nullify Resistances and Terror. Flurry with a two-handed weapon that normally takes 4 AP to attack with grants 4 attacks for the AP cost of two. The damage here is very weapon dependent, unlike with magical skills.\nApart from skills, levels in Man-at-Arms unlock more than any other ability. Remarkably, a level 5 in Man-at-Arms is not required for any skill, but unlocks the talents \"Sidewinder\" and \"Weather the Storm\".\nOriginal Sin.\nEnhanced Edition.\nThe bracket after the CD of each skill indicates the minimum cooldown (achieved when STR is 15 or higher).\n\u221e) Can only be cast once per combat."}
