{"id": "11317", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11317", "title": "Marcus Miles", "text": "Marcus Miles better known as Beast is the cousin of the dwarven queen &lt;a href=\"Justinia\"&gt;Justinia&lt;/a&gt; who was sent unto &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; in 1242 AD.\nBackground.\nA dwarven noble who had between 1233 AD and 1242 AD banded with other nobles and tried to overthrow dwarven queen Justinia. The coup was unfortunately for him a disaster and 19 of his fellow allied nobles were swiftly hanged in gallows. Unlike other nobles he was banished and left for death on some remote and deserted island. After escaping from the island he is captured by the &lt;a href=\"magisters\"&gt;magisters&lt;/a&gt;, collared and transported to Fort Joy on the \"&lt;a href=\"Merryweather\"&gt;Merryweather&lt;/a&gt;\". \nWhen \"the Merryweather\" is attacked by the &lt;a href=\"voidwoken\"&gt;voidwoken&lt;/a&gt;, Marcus manages to make it off board, landing on &lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Eye\"&gt;Reaper's Eye&lt;/a&gt; as was planned. Rather than reside within the walls of Fort Joy, he spends his time by the shipwreck on the northwest coast.\nEncounters.\nVarieties.\nFollowing table shows all the changing stats and abilities of Marcus across the locations in the game. Note that the values are for &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Difficulty\"&gt;Classic Difficulty&lt;/a&gt; in Definitive Edition which contains un-modified values of the stats."}
{"id": "11139", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11139", "title": "Mardaneus", "text": "Mardaneus is a healer living in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; in 1218 AD.\nBackground.\nMardaneus is the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Aleroth%20Healers\"&gt;Aleroth Healers&lt;/a&gt; and one of the founders of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;. When first encountered, he appears to have lost his sanity and encases &lt;a href=\"Lanilor\"&gt;Lanilor&lt;/a&gt; in ice; mistaking him for &lt;a href=\"Thelyron%20Hashnitor\"&gt;Thelyron Hashnitor&lt;/a&gt;, the demon of decay.\nAfter &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; resurrects Thelyron, it is confirmed that he was in fact possessing Mardaneus as part of a past agreement between the two of them.\nAside from the events of Divine Divinity, Mardaneus has also written books about magic, including &lt;a href=\"On%20Magic%20Obscura\"&gt;On Magic Obscura&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "11201", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11201", "title": "Mardaneus' Cellar", "text": "Mardaneus's Cellar is a location in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nFrom the cellar entrance, one has the choice of 4 doors, two to the south and two to the north. Both northern rooms contain barrels, crates and various broken items strewn across the floor as does the southeast room. The northeast room contains a lone &lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe southwest room is similar to the others, with the exception of a locked door on the southeast wall. The &lt;a href=\"Bronze%20key\"&gt;key&lt;/a&gt; to the door is on the crate to the left of the door &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; entered. Passing through this door leads to a small annex with another door to the south.\nPassing through the second door opens up into the room directly underneath &lt;a href=\"Mardaneus\"&gt;Mardaneus&lt;/a&gt;' house, with a ladder to the north-west of the room, giving entry through the trapdoor."}
{"id": "13528", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13528", "title": "Mardaneus' House", "text": "Mardaneus' house is a home in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nMardaneus' house is a 2 part single floored building with basement built in a narrow \"C\" shape located in the south western part of Aleroth. To the front of the property is the main living area and to the rear the study with a hatch to the cellar, which can also be accessed from the well to the east of the front door.\nFrom the well entrance of the &lt;a href=\"Mardaneus%27%20Cellar\"&gt;cellar&lt;/a&gt;, there are 4 rooms shooting off from it. A &lt;a href=\"rat\"&gt;rat&lt;/a&gt; can be found wandering between the rooms and in the north eastern room a lone &lt;a href=\"skeletal%20warrior\"&gt;skeletal warrior&lt;/a&gt; can be found. In the south western room a bronze key can be found on a box to the left of the doorway, which opens the door on the southern wall. Passing though both the locked door and the one following the cellar opens up into another room which contains a ladder to the hatch in the study.\nTo the west of the building is an openly fenced off apiary with a dozen beehives set in 4 banks of 3 hives, two banks running vertically at the north of the apiary and two running vertically on the western side. On the pedestal to the eastern side of the apiary, the book &lt;a href=\"How%20to%20Make%20the%20Most%20of%20Honey\"&gt;How to Make the Most of Honey&lt;/a&gt; can be found."}
