{"id": "12277", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12277", "title": "Mass Breathing Bubble", "text": "Mass Breathing Bubble is an &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Warfare%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; source skill in \"\". \nDescription.\nSkill.\nThis skill is a Source skill version of the skill &lt;a href=\"Breathing%20Bubble\"&gt;Breathing Bubble&lt;/a&gt;. Upon casting it, the effect of the \"Breathing Bubble\" skill will be applied on allies and the caster, allowing them to ignore cloud surfaces and making them immune to suffocation and silence.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into both &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Warfare%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted by combining any &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Warfare%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks out of which atleast one must be a source skillbook. Since is a mixed source skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nLocation.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from NPCs."}
